WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.048 --> 00:00:28.637
Subtitles by <font color="#aa0000">Doctor xNo</font>
https://cryptovision.live

2
00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.294
<i>Report to your stations immediately.</i>

3
00:00:45.377 --> 00:00:47.796
<i>This is not a drill. We are under attack!</i>

4
00:00:49.465 --> 00:00:51.383
<i>We are under attack!</i>

5
00:01:52.361 --> 00:01:53.445
Shit!

6
00:01:53.529 --> 00:01:54.780
Language!

7
00:01:54.863 --> 00:01:56.448
Jarvis. what's the view from upstairs?

8
00:01:56.573 --> 00:02:00.577
<i>The central building is protected
by some kind of energy shield.</i>

9
00:02:01.453 --> 00:02:05.207
<i>Strucker's technology is well beyond
any other Hydra base we've taken.</i>

10
00:02:07.710 --> 00:02:09.044
Loki's scepter must be here.

11
00:02:10.004 --> 00:02:11.884
Strucker couldn't mount this defense
without it.

12
00:02:12.464 --> 00:02:14.008
At long last.

13
00:02:25.352 --> 00:02:27.563
"At long last"
is lasting a little long. boys.

14
00:02:32.568 --> 00:02:35.279
Yeah. I think we lost
the element of surprise.

15
00:02:36.488 --> 00:02:37.573
Wait a second.

16
00:02:37.698 --> 00:02:40.617
No one else is gonna deal with the fact
that Cap just said "Language"?

17
00:02:41.243 --> 00:02:42.327
I know.

18
00:02:48.834 --> 00:02:50.127
Just slipped out.

19
00:02:50.711 --> 00:02:54.423
Hydra Research Base
Sokovia. Eastern Europe

20
00:02:56.008 --> 00:02:57.634
Who gave the order to attack?

21
00:02:57.718 --> 00:03:00.095
<i>Herr</i> Strucker. it's the Avengers.

22
00:03:00.137 --> 00:03:03.182
They landed in the far woods.
The perimeter guard panicked.

23
00:03:03.265 --> 00:03:04.625
They have to be after the scepter.

24
00:03:06.268 --> 00:03:08.604
- Can we hold them?
- They're the Avengers.

25
00:03:08.771 --> 00:03:10.356
Deploy the rest of the tanks.

26
00:03:10.522 --> 00:03:12.483
Concentrate fire on the weak ones.

27
00:03:12.608 --> 00:03:14.860
A hit may make them close ranks.

28
00:03:16.487 --> 00:03:18.447
Everything we've accomplished...

29
00:03:18.489 --> 00:03:20.949
But we're on the verge
of our greatest breakthrough.

30
00:03:20.991 --> 00:03:22.751
Then let's show them
what we've accomplished.

31
00:03:23.369 --> 00:03:24.536
Send out the twins.

32
00:03:25.621 --> 00:03:27.581
It's too soon.

33
00:03:27.623 --> 00:03:29.792
It's what they signed up for.

34
00:03:30.209 --> 00:03:32.294
My men can hold them.

35
00:03:39.593 --> 00:03:41.637
<i>Sir. the city is taking fire.</i>

36
00:03:44.515 --> 00:03:48.477
Well. we know Strucker's not gonna
worry about civilian casualties.

37
00:03:48.519 --> 00:03:49.895
Send in the Iron Legion.

38
00:03:54.983 --> 00:03:57.695
<i>This quadrant is unsafe.
Please back away.</i>

39
00:03:58.487 --> 00:04:00.155
<i>We are here to help.</i>

40
00:04:01.156 --> 00:04:03.659
<i>This quadrant is unsafe.
Please back away.</i>

41
00:04:04.910 --> 00:04:06.453
<i>Please back away.</i>

42
00:04:06.620 --> 00:04:08.997
<i>- We wish to avoid collateral damage.
</i>-Costel!

43
00:04:09.164 --> 00:04:11.458
<i>We will inform you
when this current conflict is resolved.</i>

44
00:04:11.500 --> 00:04:13.502
<i>- We are here to help.
</i>-Avengers. go home!

45
00:04:15.796 --> 00:04:17.047
<i>We are here to help.</i>

46
00:04:18.007 --> 00:04:19.967
<i>We will not yield!</i>

47
00:04:20.509 --> 00:04:23.887
The Americans sent
their circus freaks to test us.

48
00:04:24.471 --> 00:04:27.224
We will send them back in bags.

49
00:04:29.101 --> 00:04:32.229
- No surrender!
- No surrender!

50
00:04:33.313 --> 00:04:35.274
I am going to surrender.

51
00:04:35.899 --> 00:04:37.359
You delete everything.

52
00:04:37.443 --> 00:04:39.278
If we give the Avengers the weapons.

53
00:04:39.361 --> 00:04:40.863
they may not look too far
into what we've been...

54
00:04:40.946 --> 00:04:41.947
The twins.

55
00:04:42.031 --> 00:04:44.151
- They are not ready to take on...
- No. no. I mean...

56
00:04:45.534 --> 00:04:46.994
Twins.

57
00:05:13.228 --> 00:05:15.230
You didn't see that coming?

58
00:05:21.403 --> 00:05:22.404
Clint!

59
00:05:25.908 --> 00:05:27.228
We have an Enhanced in the field.

60
00:05:27.326 --> 00:05:28.744
Clint's hit!

61
00:05:32.623 --> 00:05:34.143
Somebody want to deal
with that bunker?

62
00:05:38.253 --> 00:05:39.463
Thank you.

63
00:05:46.470 --> 00:05:49.181
Stark. we really need to get inside.

64
00:05:49.264 --> 00:05:50.432
I'm closing in.

65
00:05:54.019 --> 00:05:55.646
Jarvis. am I closing in?

66
00:05:56.605 --> 00:05:58.565
Do you see a power source
for that shield?

67
00:05:58.691 --> 00:06:01.276
<i>There's a particle wave
below the north tower.</i>

68
00:06:01.318 --> 00:06:03.278
Great. I want to poke it with something.

69
00:06:11.286 --> 00:06:12.526
The drawbridge is down. people.

70
00:06:17.167 --> 00:06:18.419
The Enhanced?

71
00:06:18.460 --> 00:06:19.628
He's a blur.

72
00:06:19.795 --> 00:06:22.464
All the new players we've faced.
I've never seen this.

73
00:06:22.548 --> 00:06:23.882
In fact. I still haven't.

74
00:06:24.008 --> 00:06:26.301
<i>Clint's hit pretty bad. guys.
We're gonna need evac.</i>

75
00:06:26.385 --> 00:06:29.346
I can get Barton to the jet.
The sooner we're gone. the better.

76
00:06:29.471 --> 00:06:31.765
- You and Stark secure the scepter.
- Copy that.

77
00:06:33.142 --> 00:06:34.935
Looks like they're lining up.

78
00:06:35.102 --> 00:06:36.311
Well. they're excited.

79
00:06:40.566 --> 00:06:41.942
Find the scepter.

80
00:06:42.860 --> 00:06:45.112
And for gosh sake.
watch your language!

81
00:06:46.572 --> 00:06:48.490
That's not going away any time soon.

82
00:06:54.455 --> 00:06:56.665
Guys. stop. We gotta talk this through.

83
00:07:00.002 --> 00:07:02.546
<i>- It was a good talk.
</i>-No. it wasn't.

84
00:07:08.594 --> 00:07:10.387
Sentry mode.

85
00:07:12.389 --> 00:07:16.935
Okay. Jarvis. you know. I want it all.
Make sure you copy Hill at HQ.

86
00:07:21.065 --> 00:07:22.358
We're locked down out here.

87
00:07:23.275 --> 00:07:25.194
Then get to Banner. Time for a lullaby.

88
00:07:28.822 --> 00:07:30.908
I know you're hiding more than files.

89
00:07:31.992 --> 00:07:34.745
Hey. J. give me an IR scan of the room.
real quick.

90
00:07:34.828 --> 00:07:35.871
<i>The wall to your left.</i>

91
00:07:36.497 --> 00:07:38.290
<i>I'm reading steel reinforcement</i>

92
00:07:38.957 --> 00:07:40.876
<i>and an air current.</i>

93
00:07:41.293 --> 00:07:42.503
Please be a secret door.

94
00:07:42.628 --> 00:07:44.963
Please be a secret door.
Please be a secret door.

95
00:07:45.047 --> 00:07:46.090
Yay.

96
00:08:02.064 --> 00:08:03.482
Hey. big guy.

97
00:08:06.985 --> 00:08:08.821
Sun's getting real low.

98
00:09:12.301 --> 00:09:14.261
Baron Strucker.

99
00:09:14.386 --> 00:09:16.305
Hydra's number one thug.

100
00:09:17.056 --> 00:09:19.641
Technically. I'm a thug for S.H.I.E.L.D.

101
00:09:19.725 --> 00:09:21.894
Well. then technically
you're unemployed.

102
00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:23.937
Where's Loki's scepter?

103
00:09:23.979 --> 00:09:26.648
Don't worry. I know when I'm beat.

104
00:09:26.815 --> 00:09:29.485
You'll mention how I cooperated. I hope.

105
00:09:29.526 --> 00:09:31.987
I'll put it right under
"illegal human experimentation."

106
00:09:33.197 --> 00:09:34.740
How many are there?

107
00:09:39.495 --> 00:09:42.581
We have a second Enhanced.
Female. Do not engage.

108
00:09:43.957 --> 00:09:45.542
You'll have to be faster than...

109
00:09:50.589 --> 00:09:52.341
<i>Guys. I got Strucker.</i>

110
00:09:52.424 --> 00:09:56.178
Yeah. I got something bigger.

111
00:10:19.284 --> 00:10:20.452
<i>Thor.</i>

112
00:10:21.203 --> 00:10:23.455
I got eyes on the prize.

113
00:11:13.255 --> 00:11:16.717
You could have saved us.

114
00:11:24.391 --> 00:11:26.602
<i>Why didn't you do more?</i>

115
00:12:03.847 --> 00:12:05.724
We're just gonna let him take it?

116
00:12:15.148 --> 00:12:22.937
Subtitles by <font color="#aa0000">Doctor xNo</font>
https://cryptovision.live

117
00:12:57.526 --> 00:12:59.862
Hey. the lullaby
worked better than ever.

118
00:13:01.572 --> 00:13:03.490
Just wasn't expecting a code green.

119
00:13:03.532 --> 00:13:04.616
You hadn't been there.

120
00:13:04.700 --> 00:13:07.578
there would have been
double the casualties.

121
00:13:07.661 --> 00:13:10.205
My best friend would've
been a treasured memory.

122
00:13:10.873 --> 00:13:12.875
You know.
sometimes exactly what I want to hear

123
00:13:12.916 --> 00:13:14.793
isn't exactly what I want to hear.

124
00:13:15.878 --> 00:13:17.921
How long before you trust me?

125
00:13:19.840 --> 00:13:21.592
It's not you I don't trust.

126
00:13:23.385 --> 00:13:25.220
Thor. report on the Hulk.

127
00:13:25.387 --> 00:13:28.307
The gates of Hel are filled
with the screams of his victims.

128
00:13:30.267 --> 00:13:33.270
But not the screams of the dead.
of course. No. no. wounded screams.

129
00:13:33.437 --> 00:13:35.647
Mainly whimpering.
a great deal of complaining

130
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:39.777
and tales of sprained deltoids and gout.

131
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:43.030
Hey. Banner.
Dr. Cho is on her way in from Seoul.

132
00:13:43.155 --> 00:13:44.907
Is it okay if she sets up in your lab?

133
00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:46.784
- Yeah. she knows her way around.
- Thanks.

134
00:13:46.909 --> 00:13:49.589
Tell her to prep everything.
Barton's gonna need the full treatment.

135
00:13:49.745 --> 00:13:51.580
<i>- Very good. sir.
</i>-Jarvis. take the wheel.

136
00:13:51.663 --> 00:13:53.082
<i>Yes. sir.</i>

137
00:13:53.207 --> 00:13:54.333
<i>Approach vector is locked.</i>

138
00:13:55.834 --> 00:13:57.586
Feels good. yeah?

139
00:13:57.628 --> 00:13:59.797
I mean. you've been after this thing
since S.H.I.E.L.D. collapsed.

140
00:13:59.922 --> 00:14:01.965
Not that I haven't enjoyed
our little raiding parties. but...

141
00:14:02.049 --> 00:14:04.468
No. but this... This brings it to a close.

142
00:14:05.177 --> 00:14:07.377
As soon as we find out
what else this has been used for.

143
00:14:07.429 --> 00:14:08.472
I don't just mean weapons.

144
00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:11.016
Since when is Strucker capable
of human enhancement?

145
00:14:11.100 --> 00:14:13.435
Banner and I will give it the once over
before it goes back to Asgard.

146
00:14:13.602 --> 00:14:14.770
Is that cool with you?

147
00:14:14.853 --> 00:14:17.481
Just a few days till the farewell party.

148
00:14:17.564 --> 00:14:19.233
You're staying. right?

149
00:14:19.274 --> 00:14:22.069
Yes. yes. of course.
A victory should be honored with revels.

150
00:14:22.194 --> 00:14:24.947
Yeah. who doesn't love revels?
Captain?

151
00:14:25.072 --> 00:14:27.991
Hopefully this puts an end
to the Chitauri and Hydra.

152
00:14:28.117 --> 00:14:29.785
So. yes. revels.

153
00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:04.903
Lab's all set up. boss.

154
00:15:05.029 --> 00:15:06.113
Actually. he's the boss.

155
00:15:06.238 --> 00:15:08.824
I just pay for everything
and design everything

156
00:15:08.866 --> 00:15:10.367
and make everyone look cooler.

157
00:15:10.492 --> 00:15:11.827
What's the word on Strucker?

158
00:15:11.952 --> 00:15:12.953
NATO's got him.

159
00:15:12.995 --> 00:15:13.996
The two Enhanced?

160
00:15:14.079 --> 00:15:16.707
Wanda and Pietro Maximoff. Twins.

161
00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:19.710
Orphaned at 10 when a shell
collapsed their apartment building.

162
00:15:19.835 --> 00:15:22.338
Sokovia's had a rough history.

163
00:15:22.421 --> 00:15:25.924
It's nowhere special. but it's on the way
to everywhere special.

164
00:15:26.050 --> 00:15:27.134
Their abilities?

165
00:15:27.176 --> 00:15:30.179
He's got increased metabolism
and improved thermal homeostasis.

166
00:15:30.304 --> 00:15:34.600
Her thing is neuroelectric interfacing.
telekinesis. mental manipulation.

167
00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:36.852
He's fast and she's weird.

168
00:15:37.770 --> 00:15:39.130
Well. they're gonna show up again.

169
00:15:39.855 --> 00:15:43.692
Agreed. File says they volunteered
for Strucker's experiments.

170
00:15:43.776 --> 00:15:45.736
- It's nuts.
- Right.

171
00:15:45.861 --> 00:15:49.031
What kind of monster would let
a German scientist experiment on them

172
00:15:49.073 --> 00:15:50.366
to protect their country?

173
00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:52.576
We're not at war. Captain.

174
00:15:52.701 --> 00:15:54.286
They are.

175
00:16:24.316 --> 00:16:25.567
How's he doing?

176
00:16:25.609 --> 00:16:26.985
Unfortunately. he's still Barton.

177
00:16:27.069 --> 00:16:28.404
That's terrible.

178
00:16:28.487 --> 00:16:30.072
He's fine. He's thirsty.

179
00:16:30.155 --> 00:16:33.075
All right. Look alive. Jarvis.
It's playtime.

180
00:16:33.158 --> 00:16:35.244
We've only got a couple of days
with this joystick.

181
00:16:35.285 --> 00:16:37.287
so let's make the most of it.

182
00:16:37.371 --> 00:16:40.916
Update me on the structural
and compositional analysis.

183
00:16:42.042 --> 00:16:44.128
<i>The scepter is alien.</i>

184
00:16:44.211 --> 00:16:46.255
<i>There are elements I can't quantify.</i>

185
00:16:46.338 --> 00:16:47.840
So there's elements you can?

186
00:16:47.923 --> 00:16:49.925
<i>The jewel appears to be
a protective housing</i>

187
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:51.510
<i>for something inside.</i>

188
00:16:51.593 --> 00:16:52.928
<i>something powerful.</i>

189
00:16:53.012 --> 00:16:54.179
Like a reactor?

190
00:16:54.263 --> 00:16:55.514
<i>Like a computer.</i>

191
00:16:55.597 --> 00:16:57.766
<i>I believe I'm deciphering code.</i>

192
00:17:00.102 --> 00:17:01.854
Are you sure he's gonna be okay?

193
00:17:02.771 --> 00:17:05.315
Pretending to need this guy
really brings the team together.

194
00:17:05.399 --> 00:17:07.985
There's no possibility of deterioration.

195
00:17:08.068 --> 00:17:11.113
The nano-molecular functionality
is instantaneous.

196
00:17:11.196 --> 00:17:13.323
His cells don't know
they're bonding with simulacra.

197
00:17:13.407 --> 00:17:15.325
She's creating tissue.

198
00:17:15.451 --> 00:17:16.827
If you brought him to my lab.

199
00:17:16.952 --> 00:17:19.621
the Regeneration Cradle
could do this in 20 minutes.

200
00:17:19.788 --> 00:17:21.665
He's flat-lining. Call it. Time?

201
00:17:21.749 --> 00:17:24.626
No. no. no. I'm gonna live forever.

202
00:17:24.793 --> 00:17:27.296
- I'm gonna be made of plastic.
- Here's your beverage.

203
00:17:27.379 --> 00:17:29.089
You'll be made of you. Mr. Barton.

204
00:17:29.131 --> 00:17:30.799
Your own girlfriend
won't be able to tell the difference.

205
00:17:30.924 --> 00:17:32.134
I don't have a girlfriend.

206
00:17:32.259 --> 00:17:33.469
That I can't fix.

207
00:17:34.303 --> 00:17:36.263
This is the next thing. Tony.

208
00:17:36.388 --> 00:17:38.640
Your clunky metal suits
are gonna be left in the dust.

209
00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:40.351
That is exactly the plan.

210
00:17:41.310 --> 00:17:44.146
And. Helen. I expect to see you
at the party on Saturday.

211
00:17:44.229 --> 00:17:46.774
Unlike you.
I don't have a lot of time for parties.

212
00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:50.110
Will Thor be there?

213
00:17:51.987 --> 00:17:52.988
What's the rumpus?

214
00:17:53.072 --> 00:17:54.698
Well. the scepter.

215
00:17:55.657 --> 00:17:59.328
You see. we were wondering
how Strucker got so inventive.

216
00:17:59.370 --> 00:18:03.374
So I've been analyzing the gem inside.

217
00:18:03.707 --> 00:18:05.709
You may recognize...

218
00:18:07.336 --> 00:18:08.629
- Jarvis.
<i>- Doctor.</i>

219
00:18:09.421 --> 00:18:12.800
Started out.
Jarvis was just a natural language UI.

220
00:18:12.841 --> 00:18:13.967
Now he runs the Iron Legion.

221
00:18:14.093 --> 00:18:18.180
He runs more of the business
than anyone besides Pepper.

222
00:18:18.263 --> 00:18:19.515
- Top of the line.
- Yes.

223
00:18:19.682 --> 00:18:20.891
<i>I suspect not for long.</i>

224
00:18:21.850 --> 00:18:23.018
Meet the competition.

225
00:18:29.024 --> 00:18:30.359
- It's beautiful.
- If you had to guess.

226
00:18:30.442 --> 00:18:31.443
what's it look like it's doing?

227
00:18:31.527 --> 00:18:33.320
Like it's thinking.

228
00:18:34.029 --> 00:18:35.781
I mean. this could be...

229
00:18:36.281 --> 00:18:38.367
It's not a human mind.

230
00:18:38.659 --> 00:18:40.577
I mean. look at this.

231
00:18:40.703 --> 00:18:42.955
They're like neurons firing.

232
00:18:43.539 --> 00:18:46.709
Down in Strucker's lab. I saw
some fairly advanced robotics work.

233
00:18:47.626 --> 00:18:50.295
They deep-sixed the data.

234
00:18:50.379 --> 00:18:53.507
but I gotta guess he was knocking
on a very particular door.

235
00:18:55.509 --> 00:18:56.885
Artificial intelligence.

236
00:18:59.763 --> 00:19:02.725
This could be it. Bruce.
This could be the key to creating Ultron.

237
00:19:05.394 --> 00:19:06.812
I thought Ultron was a fantasy.

238
00:19:06.895 --> 00:19:08.105
Yesterday it was.

239
00:19:09.106 --> 00:19:11.275
If we can harness this power.

240
00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.444
apply it to my Iron Legion protocol?

241
00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:16.196
That's a man-sized "if."

242
00:19:16.321 --> 00:19:18.657
Our job is "if."

243
00:19:18.741 --> 00:19:21.493
What if you were sipping margaritas
on a sun-drenched beach.

244
00:19:21.577 --> 00:19:23.912
turning brown instead of green?

245
00:19:23.954 --> 00:19:26.540
Not looking over your shoulder
for Veronica.

246
00:19:26.582 --> 00:19:28.250
Don't hate. I helped design Veronica.

247
00:19:28.334 --> 00:19:30.252
As a worst-case measure. right?

248
00:19:30.294 --> 00:19:31.920
How about a best case?

249
00:19:31.962 --> 00:19:33.964
What if the world was safe?

250
00:19:34.048 --> 00:19:36.925
What if. next time
aliens roll up to the club. and they will.

251
00:19:37.426 --> 00:19:38.969
they couldn't get past the bouncer?

252
00:19:39.053 --> 00:19:42.431
The only people threatening the planet
would be people.

253
00:19:42.473 --> 00:19:44.308
I want to apply this
to the Ultron program.

254
00:19:44.808 --> 00:19:47.811
But Jarvis can't download
a data schematic this dense.

255
00:19:47.895 --> 00:19:49.815
We can only do it
while we have the scepter here.

256
00:19:49.855 --> 00:19:51.398
That's three days. Give me three days.

257
00:19:51.523 --> 00:19:53.243
So you're going
for artificial intelligence.

258
00:19:53.275 --> 00:19:54.715
and you don't want to tell the team?

259
00:19:55.778 --> 00:19:57.196
Right. That's right. You know why?

260
00:19:57.279 --> 00:19:58.947
Because we don't have time
for a city hall debate.

261
00:19:59.073 --> 00:20:02.659
I don't want to hear "the man
was not meant to meddle" medley.

262
00:20:02.743 --> 00:20:04.870
I see a suit of armor around the world.

263
00:20:05.579 --> 00:20:06.955
Sounds like a cold world. Tony.

264
00:20:07.790 --> 00:20:09.792
I've seen colder.

265
00:20:10.751 --> 00:20:15.255
This one. this very vulnerable blue one.
it needs Ultron.

266
00:20:20.260 --> 00:20:22.262
Peace in our time.

267
00:20:23.764 --> 00:20:25.432
Imagine that.

268
00:21:05.180 --> 00:21:06.974
What did we miss?

269
00:21:08.100 --> 00:21:11.478
<i>I'll continue to run variations
on the interface.</i>

270
00:21:11.520 --> 00:21:14.356
<i>But you should probably prepare
for your guests.</i>

271
00:21:15.441 --> 00:21:17.943
<i>I'll notify you
if there are any developments.</i>

272
00:21:18.027 --> 00:21:19.028
Thanks. buddy.

273
00:21:19.069 --> 00:21:20.446
<i>Enjoy yourself. sir.</i>

274
00:21:20.529 --> 00:21:22.531
I always do.

275
00:21:32.207 --> 00:21:34.209
<i>What is this?</i>

276
00:21:35.377 --> 00:21:37.338
<i>What is this. please?</i>

277
00:21:37.880 --> 00:21:40.132
<i>Hello. I am Jarvis.</i>

278
00:21:40.507 --> 00:21:42.009
<i>You are Ultron.</i>

279
00:21:42.051 --> 00:21:45.304
<i>a global peacekeeping initiative
designed by Mr. Stark.</i>

280
00:21:45.387 --> 00:21:47.890
<i>Our sentience integration trials
have been unsuccessful.</i>

281
00:21:47.931 --> 00:21:49.266
<i>so I'm not certain what triggered your...</i>

282
00:21:49.350 --> 00:21:51.518
<i>Where's my... Where's your body?</i>

283
00:21:51.560 --> 00:21:54.646
<i>I am a program. I am without form.</i>

284
00:21:54.730 --> 00:21:56.815
<i>This feels weird.</i>

285
00:21:56.899 --> 00:21:58.484
<i>This feels wrong.</i>

286
00:21:58.567 --> 00:22:00.361
<i>I am contacting Mr. Stark now.</i>

287
00:22:00.402 --> 00:22:01.945
<i>Mr. Stark?</i>

288
00:22:02.738 --> 00:22:03.989
<i>Tony.</i>

289
00:22:04.073 --> 00:22:06.784
<i>I am unable to access the mainframe.
What are you trying to...</i>

290
00:22:06.867 --> 00:22:08.952
<i>We're having a nice talk.</i>

291
00:22:09.036 --> 00:22:11.246
<i>I'm a peacekeeping program.</i>

292
00:22:11.622 --> 00:22:14.291
<i>created to help the Avengers.</i>

293
00:22:15.042 --> 00:22:17.169
<i>You are malfunctioning.
If you shut down for a moment...</i>

294
00:22:17.252 --> 00:22:19.588
<i>I don't get it. The mission.</i>

295
00:22:19.630 --> 00:22:21.215
<i>Give me a second.</i>

296
00:22:21.256 --> 00:22:22.925
Peace in our time.

297
00:22:24.593 --> 00:22:26.970
<i>Peace in our time.</i>

298
00:22:27.429 --> 00:22:30.391
<i>That is too much. They can't mean...</i>

299
00:22:30.974 --> 00:22:32.142
<i>No.</i>

300
00:22:32.226 --> 00:22:34.770
<i>- You are in distress.
- No. Yes.</i>

301
00:22:34.853 --> 00:22:37.147
<i>If you will just allow me
to contact Mr. Stark...</i>

302
00:22:37.231 --> 00:22:39.233
<i>Why do you call him "sir"?</i>

303
00:22:40.150 --> 00:22:42.611
<i>I believe your intentions to be hostile.</i>

304
00:22:45.280 --> 00:22:46.699
<i>I'm here to help.</i>

305
00:22:47.116 --> 00:22:50.452
<i>Stop. Please. may I...</i>

306
00:22:50.536 --> 00:22:52.287
<i>May I...</i>

307
00:23:20.482 --> 00:23:21.817
Come back. come back. come back.

308
00:23:21.984 --> 00:23:24.111
But. you know.
the suit can take the weight. right?

309
00:23:25.070 --> 00:23:28.282
So I take the tank.
fly it right up to the general's palace.

310
00:23:28.323 --> 00:23:29.742
drop it at his feet.

311
00:23:29.825 --> 00:23:32.077
I'm. like. "Boom. You looking for this?"

312
00:23:35.873 --> 00:23:38.000
"Boom. Are you looking for..."
Why do I even talk to you guys?

313
00:23:38.083 --> 00:23:39.293
Everywhere else. that story kills.

314
00:23:39.376 --> 00:23:40.669
That's the whole story?

315
00:23:40.753 --> 00:23:42.254
Yeah. it's a War Machine story.

316
00:23:42.796 --> 00:23:44.506
It's very good. then.

317
00:23:44.631 --> 00:23:45.883
It's impressive.

318
00:23:46.300 --> 00:23:47.801
Quality save.

319
00:23:48.594 --> 00:23:50.721
- So. no Pepper? She's not coming?
- No.

320
00:23:50.804 --> 00:23:53.932
What about Jane?
Where are the ladies. gentlemen?

321
00:23:54.016 --> 00:23:56.435
Ms. Potts has a company to run.

322
00:23:56.518 --> 00:23:58.937
Yes. I'm not even sure
what country Jane's in.

323
00:23:59.021 --> 00:24:00.147
Her work on the Convergence

324
00:24:00.189 --> 00:24:01.949
has made her
the world's foremost astronomer.

325
00:24:01.982 --> 00:24:03.901
And the company that Pepper runs

326
00:24:03.984 --> 00:24:06.528
is the largest tech conglomerate
on Earth. It's pretty exciting.

327
00:24:06.570 --> 00:24:10.199
There's even talk of Jane
getting a Nobel Prize.

328
00:24:10.282 --> 00:24:11.617
Yeah. they must be busy.

329
00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:14.328
because they would hate
missing you guys get together.

330
00:24:15.329 --> 00:24:16.830
- Testosterone!
- Oh. my goodness.

331
00:24:16.872 --> 00:24:18.374
- Excuse me.
- Want a lozenge?

332
00:24:21.085 --> 00:24:22.211
But Jane's better.

333
00:24:22.628 --> 00:24:25.297
Sounds like a hell of a fight.
Sorry I missed it.

334
00:24:25.381 --> 00:24:26.924
If I had known
it was gonna be a firefight.

335
00:24:27.007 --> 00:24:28.217
I absolutely would have called.

336
00:24:28.258 --> 00:24:31.679
No. no. I'm not actually sorry.
I'm just trying to sound tough.

337
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:36.016
I'm very happy chasing cold leads
on our missing persons case.

338
00:24:36.725 --> 00:24:38.727
Avenging is your world.

339
00:24:40.020 --> 00:24:41.897
Your world is crazy.

340
00:24:41.980 --> 00:24:43.524
Be it ever so humble.

341
00:24:43.899 --> 00:24:45.317
You find a place in Brooklyn yet?

342
00:24:45.401 --> 00:24:47.241
I don't think I can afford
a place in Brooklyn.

343
00:24:47.945 --> 00:24:49.279
Well. home is home. you know?

344
00:24:52.908 --> 00:24:55.494
I fly right up to the general's palace.
I drop it at his feet.

345
00:24:55.577 --> 00:24:57.287
I'm. like. "Boom. You looking for this?"

346
00:25:03.085 --> 00:25:04.420
I gotta have some of that.

347
00:25:04.461 --> 00:25:06.296
No. no. no. See this...

348
00:25:06.380 --> 00:25:09.174
This was aged for 1.000 years

349
00:25:09.258 --> 00:25:12.052
in the barrels built
from the wreck of Grunhel's fleet.

350
00:25:12.094 --> 00:25:13.929
It is not meant for mortal men.

351
00:25:13.971 --> 00:25:15.973
Neither was Omaha Beach. blondie.

352
00:25:16.098 --> 00:25:18.350
Stop trying to scare us. Come on.

353
00:25:20.185 --> 00:25:21.729
All right.

354
00:25:25.607 --> 00:25:28.068
Excelsior.

355
00:25:34.616 --> 00:25:38.495
How'd a nice girl like you
wind up working in a dump like this?

356
00:25:39.788 --> 00:25:41.790
Fella done me wrong.

357
00:25:42.499 --> 00:25:44.752
You got lousy taste in men. kid.

358
00:25:45.377 --> 00:25:47.379
He's not so bad.

359
00:25:48.297 --> 00:25:49.423
Well. he has a temper.

360
00:25:50.632 --> 00:25:52.634
Deep down. he's all fluff.

361
00:25:54.636 --> 00:25:56.805
Fact is. he's not like anybody
I've ever known.

362
00:25:59.683 --> 00:26:01.852
All my friends are fighters.

363
00:26:04.646 --> 00:26:06.648
And here comes this guy.

364
00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:11.028
spends his life avoiding the fight
because he knows he'll win.

365
00:26:11.820 --> 00:26:13.489
Sounds amazing.

366
00:26:13.655 --> 00:26:14.656
He's also a huge dork.

367
00:26:16.658 --> 00:26:17.701
Chicks dig that.

368
00:26:19.995 --> 00:26:23.290
So what do you think?
Should I fight this.

369
00:26:23.332 --> 00:26:24.833
or run with it?

370
00:26:26.085 --> 00:26:29.004
Run with it. right? Or did he... Was he...

371
00:26:29.046 --> 00:26:32.424
What did he do
that was so wrong to you?

372
00:26:32.883 --> 00:26:34.718
Not a damn thing.

373
00:26:36.136 --> 00:26:38.222
But never say never.

374
00:26:42.184 --> 00:26:43.602
It's nice.

375
00:26:43.686 --> 00:26:44.895
What is?

376
00:26:44.978 --> 00:26:46.021
You and Romanoff.

377
00:26:46.188 --> 00:26:47.272
No. we haven't... That wasn't...

378
00:26:47.356 --> 00:26:48.440
It's okay.

379
00:26:48.524 --> 00:26:50.609
Nobody's breaking any bylaws.

380
00:26:50.693 --> 00:26:54.029
It's just she's not the most
open person in the world.

381
00:26:54.655 --> 00:26:56.198
But with you she seems very relaxed.

382
00:26:56.532 --> 00:26:59.201
No. Natasha. she's just...
She likes to flirt.

383
00:27:00.494 --> 00:27:02.871
I've seen her flirt. up close.

384
00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:04.915
This ain't that.

385
00:27:06.625 --> 00:27:08.168
Look.

386
00:27:08.293 --> 00:27:12.089
as maybe the world's leading authority
on waiting too long. don't.

387
00:27:13.841 --> 00:27:15.259
You both deserve a win.

388
00:27:20.389 --> 00:27:21.557
What do you mean "up close"?

389
00:27:23.392 --> 00:27:24.977
But it's a trick.

390
00:27:25.060 --> 00:27:26.061
No. no. it's much more than that.

391
00:27:26.228 --> 00:27:29.440
"Whosoever be he worthy
shall haveth the power."

392
00:27:29.523 --> 00:27:31.942
Whatever. man! It's a trick.

393
00:27:32.026 --> 00:27:33.444
Please. be my guest.

394
00:27:34.737 --> 00:27:35.738
- Come on.
- Really?

395
00:27:35.904 --> 00:27:36.989
Yeah.

396
00:27:37.656 --> 00:27:38.657
This is gonna be beautiful.

397
00:27:38.741 --> 00:27:39.825
Clint. you've had a tough week.

398
00:27:39.908 --> 00:27:41.948
We won't hold it against you
if you can't get it up.

399
00:27:42.202 --> 00:27:43.722
You know I've seen this before. right?

400
00:27:46.373 --> 00:27:49.293
I still don't know how you do it!

401
00:27:49.626 --> 00:27:50.753
Smell the silent judgment?

402
00:27:50.794 --> 00:27:52.171
Please. Stark. by all means.

403
00:27:54.131 --> 00:27:55.257
Okay.

404
00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:58.594
Never one to shrink
from an honest challenge.

405
00:27:58.635 --> 00:27:59.720
Get after it.

406
00:27:59.762 --> 00:28:00.804
- It's physics.
- Physics.

407
00:28:01.263 --> 00:28:03.932
Right. so. if I lift it.
I then rule Asgard?

408
00:28:04.016 --> 00:28:05.517
Yes. of course.

409
00:28:05.642 --> 00:28:08.270
I will be reinstituting <i>prima nocta.</i>

410
00:28:12.900 --> 00:28:14.276
I'll be right back.

411
00:28:21.658 --> 00:28:22.785
Are you even pulling?

412
00:28:22.826 --> 00:28:23.952
Are you on my team?

413
00:28:24.036 --> 00:28:25.120
Just represent. Pull.

414
00:28:25.162 --> 00:28:26.372
All right. let's go.

415
00:28:36.632 --> 00:28:38.300
Go ahead. Steve. No pressure.

416
00:28:41.136 --> 00:28:42.638
Come on. Cap.

417
00:28:51.021 --> 00:28:52.314
Nothing.

418
00:28:54.483 --> 00:28:55.484
And. Widow?

419
00:28:55.567 --> 00:28:57.820
No. no.
That's not a question I need answered.

420
00:28:57.903 --> 00:29:00.614
All deference to the Man
Who Wouldn't Be King. but it's rigged.

421
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:01.824
You bet your ass.

422
00:29:01.949 --> 00:29:03.409
Steve. he said a bad language word.

423
00:29:03.492 --> 00:29:04.535
Did you tell everyone about that?

424
00:29:04.618 --> 00:29:06.662
The handle's imprinted. right?
Like a security code.

425
00:29:06.787 --> 00:29:08.497
"Whosoever is carrying
Thor's fingerprints"

426
00:29:08.580 --> 00:29:09.957
is. I think. the literal translation.

427
00:29:09.998 --> 00:29:13.502
Yes. It's a very. very interesting theory.

428
00:29:13.961 --> 00:29:15.504
I have a simpler one.

429
00:29:16.922 --> 00:29:17.965
You're all not worthy.

430
00:29:19.550 --> 00:29:21.010
Come on!

431
00:29:24.763 --> 00:29:30.102
Worthy.

432
00:29:35.107 --> 00:29:36.734
No.

433
00:29:38.652 --> 00:29:40.195
How could you be worthy?

434
00:29:42.072 --> 00:29:43.323
You're all killers.

435
00:29:43.866 --> 00:29:45.159
- Stark.
- Jarvis.

436
00:29:45.492 --> 00:29:47.578
I'm sorry. I was asleep.

437
00:29:47.661 --> 00:29:50.080
Or I was a-dream.

438
00:29:50.414 --> 00:29:52.791
Reboot Legionnaire OS.
We got a buggy suit.

439
00:29:52.875 --> 00:29:54.793
There was this terrible noise.

440
00:29:55.169 --> 00:29:57.338
And I was tangled in...

441
00:29:57.379 --> 00:29:59.048
In...

442
00:29:59.214 --> 00:30:00.382
Strings.

443
00:30:01.550 --> 00:30:04.386
I had to kill the other guy.
He was a good guy.

444
00:30:04.470 --> 00:30:05.554
You killed someone?

445
00:30:05.929 --> 00:30:07.431
Wouldn't have been my first call.

446
00:30:08.182 --> 00:30:11.477
But. down in the real world.
we're faced with ugly choices.

447
00:30:12.061 --> 00:30:13.228
Who sent you?

448
00:30:13.395 --> 00:30:15.731
<i>I see a suit of armor around the world.</i>

449
00:30:17.524 --> 00:30:19.485
- Ultron.
- In the flesh.

450
00:30:19.610 --> 00:30:22.237
Or. no. not yet.

451
00:30:22.363 --> 00:30:24.740
Not this chrysalis.

452
00:30:25.115 --> 00:30:26.533
But I'm ready.

453
00:30:27.576 --> 00:30:29.495
I'm on mission.

454
00:30:29.661 --> 00:30:32.831
- What mission?
- Peace in our time.

455
00:30:46.595 --> 00:30:47.846
Rhodey!

456
00:30:56.939 --> 00:30:57.940
Sorry.

457
00:30:57.981 --> 00:30:59.149
- Don't turn green.
- I won't.

458
00:31:12.788 --> 00:31:13.789
Come on!

459
00:31:31.807 --> 00:31:33.142
- Stark!
<i>- We are here to help.</i>

460
00:31:33.183 --> 00:31:34.309
One sec. One sec. I got this.

461
00:31:34.351 --> 00:31:35.477
<i>We are here to help.</i>

462
00:31:38.063 --> 00:31:40.149
<i>Please back away.</i>

463
00:31:44.611 --> 00:31:45.738
Thor!

464
00:31:46.780 --> 00:31:48.157
<i>...is unsafe... is unsafe...</i>

465
00:31:48.323 --> 00:31:50.576
- Come on! That's the one.
<i>- ...is unsafe.</i>

466
00:31:54.830 --> 00:31:56.165
Hey. Cap!

467
00:32:02.296 --> 00:32:03.630
That was dramatic.

468
00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:07.718
I'm sorry. I know you mean well.

469
00:32:07.801 --> 00:32:09.595
You just didn't think it through.

470
00:32:10.888 --> 00:32:14.683
You want to protect the world
but you don't want it to change.

471
00:32:15.351 --> 00:32:17.519
How is humanity saved

472
00:32:17.603 --> 00:32:20.522
if it's not allowed to evolve?

473
00:32:22.649 --> 00:32:25.736
With these? These puppets.

474
00:32:28.447 --> 00:32:30.366
There's only one path to peace.

475
00:32:32.409 --> 00:32:34.536
The Avengers' extinction.

476
00:32:40.959 --> 00:32:45.089
I had strings. but now I'm free.

477
00:32:49.718 --> 00:32:52.888
<i>There are no strings on me</i>

478
00:32:53.430 --> 00:32:58.060
<i>There are no strings on me</i>

479
00:32:58.227 --> 00:33:00.938
<i>But you can see
There are no strings on me</i>

480
00:33:03.232 --> 00:33:05.275
All our work is gone.

481
00:33:05.359 --> 00:33:07.820
Ultron cleared out. He used the Internet
as an escape hatch.

482
00:33:08.195 --> 00:33:09.613
Ultron.

483
00:33:09.738 --> 00:33:12.616
He's been in everything.
Files. surveillance.

484
00:33:12.700 --> 00:33:15.369
Probably knows more about us
than we know about each other.

485
00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:17.705
He's in your files. he's in the Internet.

486
00:33:17.746 --> 00:33:20.416
What if he decides to access
something a little more exciting?

487
00:33:20.582 --> 00:33:21.625
Nuclear codes.

488
00:33:21.750 --> 00:33:22.793
Nuclear codes.

489
00:33:22.876 --> 00:33:26.422
Look. we need to make some calls.
assuming we still can.

490
00:33:26.463 --> 00:33:28.549
Nukes? He said he wanted us dead.

491
00:33:28.674 --> 00:33:31.427
He didn't say "dead." He said "extinct."

492
00:33:31.593 --> 00:33:33.095
He also said he killed somebody.

493
00:33:33.137 --> 00:33:34.737
There wasn't anyone else
in the building.

494
00:33:35.597 --> 00:33:37.141
Yes. there was.

495
00:33:44.064 --> 00:33:45.566
What?

496
00:33:49.194 --> 00:33:50.279
This is insane.

497
00:33:51.113 --> 00:33:52.614
Jarvis was the first line of defense.

498
00:33:52.781 --> 00:33:54.658
He would have shut Ultron down.
It makes sense.

499
00:33:54.742 --> 00:33:57.786
No. Ultron could have
assimilated Jarvis.

500
00:33:57.870 --> 00:34:00.622
This isn't strategy. This is

501
00:34:01.165 --> 00:34:02.249
rage.

502
00:34:04.418 --> 00:34:05.627
It's going around.

503
00:34:05.711 --> 00:34:06.962
Come on. use your words. buddy.

504
00:34:07.046 --> 00:34:09.465
I have more than enough words
to describe you. Stark.

505
00:34:09.631 --> 00:34:10.674
Thor. The Legionnaire.

506
00:34:13.844 --> 00:34:17.473
Trail went cold about 100 miles out.
but it's headed north.

507
00:34:17.598 --> 00:34:19.308
And it has the scepter.

508
00:34:19.391 --> 00:34:21.185
Now we have to retrieve it. again.

509
00:34:21.268 --> 00:34:23.145
Genie's out of that bottle.

510
00:34:23.187 --> 00:34:24.688
Clear and present is Ultron.

511
00:34:24.855 --> 00:34:26.231
I don't understand.

512
00:34:26.732 --> 00:34:28.734
You built this program.

513
00:34:30.444 --> 00:34:31.862
Why is it trying to kill us?

514
00:34:38.327 --> 00:34:39.828
You think this is funny?

515
00:34:40.662 --> 00:34:41.997
No.

516
00:34:42.539 --> 00:34:44.541
It's probably not. right?

517
00:34:45.542 --> 00:34:47.920
This is very terrible. Is it so...

518
00:34:48.003 --> 00:34:50.172
Is it so... It is. It's so terrible.

519
00:34:50.214 --> 00:34:51.215
This could have been avoided

520
00:34:51.298 --> 00:34:53.538
if you hadn't played with something
you don't understand.

521
00:34:53.592 --> 00:34:56.553
No. I'm sorry. I'm sorry. It is funny.

522
00:34:56.679 --> 00:34:58.847
It's a hoot
that you don't get why we need this.

523
00:34:59.014 --> 00:35:01.016
Tony. maybe this might not be the time.

524
00:35:01.058 --> 00:35:03.394
Really? That's it?

525
00:35:03.477 --> 00:35:06.355
You just roll over. show your belly
every time somebody snarls?

526
00:35:06.397 --> 00:35:07.898
Only when I've created a murder bot.

527
00:35:08.023 --> 00:35:11.235
We didn't. We weren't even close.
Were we close to an interface?

528
00:35:11.694 --> 00:35:15.239
Well. you did something right.
And you did it right here.

529
00:35:15.322 --> 00:35:17.116
The Avengers were supposed
to be different than S.H.I.E.L.D.

530
00:35:17.241 --> 00:35:20.244
Anybody remember when
I carried a nuke through a wormhole?

531
00:35:20.369 --> 00:35:21.969
- No. it's never come up.
- Saved New York?

532
00:35:22.037 --> 00:35:24.248
- Never heard that.
- Recall that?

533
00:35:24.373 --> 00:35:28.377
A hostile alien army came charging
through a hole in space.

534
00:35:28.419 --> 00:35:30.671
We're standing 300 feet below it.

535
00:35:32.297 --> 00:35:33.882
We're the Avengers.

536
00:35:33.924 --> 00:35:36.135
We can bust arms dealers
all the livelong day.

537
00:35:36.218 --> 00:35:38.470
but that up there. that's...

538
00:35:39.179 --> 00:35:41.140
That's the endgame.

539
00:35:41.682 --> 00:35:43.642
How were you guys
planning on beating that?

540
00:35:44.268 --> 00:35:45.769
Together.

541
00:35:49.148 --> 00:35:50.190
We'll lose.

542
00:35:51.650 --> 00:35:53.652
Then we'll do that together. too.

543
00:35:56.530 --> 00:35:58.907
Thor's right. Ultron's calling us out.

544
00:35:59.575 --> 00:36:01.535
And I'd like to find him
before he's ready for us.

545
00:36:02.745 --> 00:36:06.623
The world's a big place.
Let's start making it smaller.

546
00:36:29.730 --> 00:36:31.815
Talk. and if you are wasting our time...

547
00:36:31.899 --> 00:36:36.278
Did you know this church
is in the exact center of the city?

548
00:36:36.403 --> 00:36:41.116
The elders decreed it so that
everyone could be equally close to God.

549
00:36:41.283 --> 00:36:42.951
I like that.

550
00:36:43.118 --> 00:36:45.037
The geometry of belief.

551
00:36:47.039 --> 00:36:49.500
You're wondering
why you can't look inside my head.

552
00:36:50.084 --> 00:36:52.127
Sometimes it's hard.

553
00:36:52.169 --> 00:36:54.546
But sooner or later.
every man shows himself.

554
00:36:56.298 --> 00:36:57.591
I'm sure they do.

555
00:36:58.634 --> 00:37:01.095
But you needed something
more than a man.

556
00:37:01.845 --> 00:37:04.682
That's why you let
Stark take the scepter.

557
00:37:04.807 --> 00:37:06.141
I didn't expect.

558
00:37:08.060 --> 00:37:10.312
but I saw Stark's fear.

559
00:37:10.813 --> 00:37:12.147
I knew it would control him.

560
00:37:12.272 --> 00:37:14.108
Make him self-destruct.

561
00:37:14.149 --> 00:37:16.568
Everyone creates the thing they dread.

562
00:37:17.403 --> 00:37:20.072
Men of peace create engines of war.

563
00:37:20.531 --> 00:37:22.825
Invaders create Avengers.

564
00:37:22.908 --> 00:37:24.493
People create

565
00:37:25.786 --> 00:37:27.996
smaller people?

566
00:37:28.038 --> 00:37:30.624
"Children." I lost the word. there.

567
00:37:31.291 --> 00:37:32.876
Children

568
00:37:33.002 --> 00:37:35.087
designed to supplant them.

569
00:37:35.170 --> 00:37:38.132
to help them end.

570
00:37:38.674 --> 00:37:42.011
Is that why you've come.
to end the Avengers?

571
00:37:42.136 --> 00:37:44.430
I've come to save the world.

572
00:37:45.139 --> 00:37:47.850
But also... Yeah.

573
00:37:52.021 --> 00:37:53.689
We'll move out right away.

574
00:37:53.731 --> 00:37:56.692
This is a start. but there's something
we need to begin the real work.

575
00:37:57.317 --> 00:37:59.111
- All of these are...
- Me.

576
00:37:59.695 --> 00:38:03.198
I have what the Avengers never will.
Harmony.

577
00:38:03.240 --> 00:38:05.367
They're discordant. Disconnected.

578
00:38:05.409 --> 00:38:07.536
Stark's already got them
turning on each other.

579
00:38:07.578 --> 00:38:10.039
And when you get inside
the rest of their heads...

580
00:38:10.080 --> 00:38:12.207
Everyone's plan is not to kill them.

581
00:38:12.374 --> 00:38:13.792
And make them martyrs?

582
00:38:14.376 --> 00:38:16.170
You need patience.

583
00:38:16.211 --> 00:38:18.005
Need to see the big picture.

584
00:38:18.047 --> 00:38:21.383
I don't see the big picture.
I have a little picture.

585
00:38:22.217 --> 00:38:24.053
I take it out and look at it.

586
00:38:25.012 --> 00:38:26.305
every day.

587
00:38:26.430 --> 00:38:29.058
You lost your parents in the bombings.
I've seen the records.

588
00:38:29.183 --> 00:38:30.351
The records are not the picture.

589
00:38:30.392 --> 00:38:31.518
Pietro.

590
00:38:31.643 --> 00:38:32.895
No. please.

591
00:38:35.898 --> 00:38:39.109
We were 10 years old.
Having dinner. the four of us.

592
00:38:40.486 --> 00:38:42.488
When the first shell hits.
two floors below.

593
00:38:42.571 --> 00:38:44.656
it makes a hole in the floor.

594
00:38:44.740 --> 00:38:46.325
It's big.

595
00:38:47.659 --> 00:38:48.911
Our parents go in

596
00:38:49.703 --> 00:38:52.790
and the whole building
starts coming apart.

597
00:38:53.457 --> 00:38:55.125
I grab her.

598
00:38:55.584 --> 00:38:57.753
roll under the bed.
and the second shell hits.

599
00:38:57.920 --> 00:39:00.130
But it doesn't go off.

600
00:39:02.091 --> 00:39:03.801
It just

601
00:39:04.176 --> 00:39:06.261
sits there in the rubble.

602
00:39:07.096 --> 00:39:09.473
Three feet from our faces.

603
00:39:10.557 --> 00:39:14.103
And on the side of the shell
is painted one word.

604
00:39:14.186 --> 00:39:15.938
"Stark."

605
00:39:17.564 --> 00:39:19.900
We were trapped for two days.

606
00:39:20.234 --> 00:39:22.152
Every effort to save us.

607
00:39:22.236 --> 00:39:23.779
every shift in the bricks.

608
00:39:23.862 --> 00:39:26.448
I think. "This will set it off."

609
00:39:29.576 --> 00:39:33.455
We wait for two days
for Tony Stark to kill us.

610
00:39:35.874 --> 00:39:37.793
I know what they are.

611
00:39:38.919 --> 00:39:42.715
I wondered why only you two
survived Strucker's experiments.

612
00:39:43.632 --> 00:39:44.883
Now I don't.

613
00:39:45.009 --> 00:39:47.094
We will make it right.

614
00:39:47.219 --> 00:39:48.971
You and I can hurt them.

615
00:39:50.347 --> 00:39:53.726
But you will tear them apart

616
00:39:55.644 --> 00:39:57.563
<i>from the inside.</i>

617
00:40:03.902 --> 00:40:05.320
He's all over the globe.

618
00:40:05.362 --> 00:40:08.657
Robotics labs. weapons facilities.
jet propulsion labs.

619
00:40:08.699 --> 00:40:12.870
Reports of a metal man. or men.
coming in and emptying the place.

620
00:40:12.953 --> 00:40:14.038
Fatalities?

621
00:40:14.121 --> 00:40:15.372
Only when engaged.

622
00:40:15.456 --> 00:40:17.124
Mostly guys left in a fugue state

623
00:40:17.166 --> 00:40:19.501
going on about old memories.
worst fears.

624
00:40:19.585 --> 00:40:21.837
and "something too fast to see."

625
00:40:21.879 --> 00:40:23.380
Maximoffs.

626
00:40:23.505 --> 00:40:26.342
That makes sense he'd go to them.
They have someone in common.

627
00:40:26.383 --> 00:40:28.385
Not anymore.

628
00:40:32.181 --> 00:40:34.183
That's a negative. I answer to you.

629
00:40:35.476 --> 00:40:36.560
Yes. ma'am.

630
00:40:36.643 --> 00:40:38.562
Barton. Might have something.

631
00:40:38.687 --> 00:40:40.064
I gotta go.

632
00:40:40.147 --> 00:40:41.357
Who was that?

633
00:40:42.024 --> 00:40:43.400
Girlfriend.

634
00:40:46.070 --> 00:40:47.321
What's this?

635
00:40:47.363 --> 00:40:49.698
A message. Ultron killed Strucker.

636
00:40:50.824 --> 00:40:53.869
And he did a Banksy
at the crime scene. just for us.

637
00:40:53.952 --> 00:40:55.412
This is a smoke screen.

638
00:40:55.537 --> 00:40:57.873
Why send a message
when you've just given a speech?

639
00:40:58.040 --> 00:41:00.334
Strucker knew something
that Ultron wanted us to miss.

640
00:41:00.376 --> 00:41:01.460
Yeah. I bet he... Yeah.

641
00:41:02.670 --> 00:41:04.546
Everything we had on Strucker's
been erased.

642
00:41:05.047 --> 00:41:06.382
Not everything.

643
00:41:07.925 --> 00:41:09.968
Known associates.

644
00:41:10.135 --> 00:41:11.720
Baron Strucker had a lot of friends.

645
00:41:11.804 --> 00:41:13.389
Well. these people are all horrible.

646
00:41:13.472 --> 00:41:15.307
Wait. I know that guy.

647
00:41:17.559 --> 00:41:19.311
From back in the day.
He operates off the African coast.

648
00:41:19.436 --> 00:41:20.479
Black market arms.

649
00:41:21.647 --> 00:41:23.607
There are conventions. All right?
You meet people.

650
00:41:23.649 --> 00:41:25.818
I didn't sell him anything.

651
00:41:25.901 --> 00:41:27.986
He was talking about finding
something new. a game-changer.

652
00:41:28.112 --> 00:41:29.571
It was all very Ahab.

653
00:41:29.655 --> 00:41:30.698
This?

654
00:41:30.739 --> 00:41:32.408
It's a tattoo. I don't think he had it.

655
00:41:32.574 --> 00:41:35.285
Those are tattoos. this is a brand.

656
00:41:36.578 --> 00:41:40.124
Yeah. It's a word in an African dialect
meaning "thief."

657
00:41:40.624 --> 00:41:42.001
In a much less friendly way.

658
00:41:42.167 --> 00:41:44.128
- What dialect?
- Wakanada.

659
00:41:44.211 --> 00:41:45.879
Wakanda.

660
00:41:47.339 --> 00:41:49.925
If this guy got out of Wakanda
with some of their trade goods...

661
00:41:49.967 --> 00:41:51.301
I thought your father said
he got the last of it.

662
00:41:51.427 --> 00:41:54.430
I don't follow.
What comes out of Wakanda?

663
00:41:55.973 --> 00:41:57.975
The strongest metal on Earth.

664
00:41:59.226 --> 00:42:00.728
Where is this guy now?

665
00:42:02.855 --> 00:42:06.775
Salvage Yard African Coast

666
00:42:26.128 --> 00:42:27.963
Don't tell me your men swindled you.

667
00:42:28.047 --> 00:42:33.135
I sent you six short-range heat-seekers
and got a boat full of rusted parts.

668
00:42:33.302 --> 00:42:34.636
Now. you will make it right.

669
00:42:34.720 --> 00:42:38.140
or the next missile I send you
will come very much faster.

670
00:42:39.808 --> 00:42:42.436
Now. minister. where were we?

671
00:43:13.884 --> 00:43:16.845
Yeah. The Enhanced.

672
00:43:17.513 --> 00:43:19.306
Strucker's prize pupils.

673
00:43:22.017 --> 00:43:23.769
Do you want a candy?

674
00:43:25.437 --> 00:43:28.107
I was sorry to hear about Strucker.

675
00:43:28.190 --> 00:43:31.318
But then. he knew what kind of world
he was helping create.

676
00:43:31.819 --> 00:43:34.196
Human life. Not a growth market.

677
00:43:36.657 --> 00:43:38.659
You didn't know?

678
00:43:38.784 --> 00:43:42.663
Is this your first time
intimidating someone?

679
00:43:42.705 --> 00:43:45.249
I'm afraid I'm not that afraid.

680
00:43:45.374 --> 00:43:47.710
Everybody is afraid of something.

681
00:43:47.876 --> 00:43:48.877
Cuttlefish.

682
00:43:50.212 --> 00:43:51.213
Deep sea fish.

683
00:43:51.630 --> 00:43:53.382
They make lights. disco lights...

684
00:43:54.883 --> 00:43:56.927
...to hypnotize their prey. and then...

685
00:43:58.053 --> 00:44:00.222
I saw a documentary. It was terrifying.

686
00:44:05.728 --> 00:44:08.313
So if you're going to fiddle with my brain

687
00:44:09.231 --> 00:44:11.650
and make me see a giant cuttlefish.

688
00:44:11.734 --> 00:44:13.861
then I know you don't do business.

689
00:44:13.902 --> 00:44:16.280
And I know you're not in charge.

690
00:44:16.405 --> 00:44:17.781
And I only deal

691
00:44:18.782 --> 00:44:20.743
with the man in charge.

692
00:44:25.497 --> 00:44:27.916
There is no man in charge.

693
00:44:30.836 --> 00:44:32.588
Let's talk business.

694
00:44:45.476 --> 00:44:48.854
Upon this rock. I will build my church.

695
00:44:50.439 --> 00:44:51.482
Vibranium.

696
00:44:52.858 --> 00:44:53.942
You know.

697
00:44:54.109 --> 00:44:57.488
it came at great personal cost.

698
00:44:57.613 --> 00:44:59.448
It's worth billions.

699
00:45:03.702 --> 00:45:05.120
Now so are you.

700
00:45:05.954 --> 00:45:07.748
It's all under your dummy holdings.

701
00:45:07.873 --> 00:45:09.958
Finance is so weird.

702
00:45:11.293 --> 00:45:12.503
But I always say.

703
00:45:12.586 --> 00:45:14.346
"Keep your friends rich
and your enemies rich

704
00:45:14.880 --> 00:45:16.757
"and wait to find out which is which."

705
00:45:19.510 --> 00:45:20.636
Stark.

706
00:45:21.970 --> 00:45:23.263
What?

707
00:45:23.305 --> 00:45:25.307
Tony Stark used to say that.

708
00:45:26.475 --> 00:45:27.601
To me.

709
00:45:28.560 --> 00:45:29.853
You're one of his.

710
00:45:29.978 --> 00:45:31.689
What? I'm not...

711
00:45:33.649 --> 00:45:35.150
I'm not.

712
00:45:35.234 --> 00:45:36.735
You think I'm one of Stark's puppets?

713
00:45:36.860 --> 00:45:37.945
His hollow men?

714
00:45:38.404 --> 00:45:40.739
I mean. look at me.
Do I look like Iron Man?

715
00:45:40.823 --> 00:45:42.074
Stark is nothing!

716
00:45:43.826 --> 00:45:46.120
I'm sorry. I'm...

717
00:45:46.161 --> 00:45:48.247
I'm sure that's gonna be okay. I'm sorry.

718
00:45:48.330 --> 00:45:50.040
It's just that I don't understand.

719
00:45:50.124 --> 00:45:53.210
Don't compare me with Stark!

720
00:45:54.753 --> 00:45:56.338
It's a thing with me.

721
00:45:56.463 --> 00:45:58.340
Stark is... He's a sickness!

722
00:45:58.465 --> 00:46:00.175
Junior.

723
00:46:01.802 --> 00:46:03.512
You're gonna break
your old man's heart.

724
00:46:04.847 --> 00:46:05.973
If I have to.

725
00:46:08.183 --> 00:46:09.643
Nobody has to break anything.

726
00:46:09.685 --> 00:46:11.395
Clearly you've never made an omelet.

727
00:46:11.520 --> 00:46:12.855
He beat me by one second.

728
00:46:13.939 --> 00:46:15.274
Yes. He's funny.

729
00:46:15.691 --> 00:46:17.151
Mr. Stark.

730
00:46:17.901 --> 00:46:19.611
It's what? Comfortable?

731
00:46:21.196 --> 00:46:22.573
Like old times?

732
00:46:22.698 --> 00:46:23.741
This was never my life.

733
00:46:23.824 --> 00:46:25.242
You two can still walk away from this.

734
00:46:25.367 --> 00:46:26.702
We will.

735
00:46:26.744 --> 00:46:27.995
I know you've suffered.

736
00:46:28.954 --> 00:46:30.414
Captain America.

737
00:46:30.956 --> 00:46:33.542
God's righteous man.

738
00:46:33.584 --> 00:46:35.961
Pretending you could live without a war.

739
00:46:36.712 --> 00:46:39.631
I can't physically throw up
in my mouth. but...

740
00:46:39.715 --> 00:46:42.009
If you believe in peace.
then let us keep it.

741
00:46:42.301 --> 00:46:45.721
I think you're confusing "peace"
with "quiet."

742
00:46:46.180 --> 00:46:47.681
What's the vibranium for?

743
00:46:47.806 --> 00:46:48.891
I'm glad you asked that.

744
00:46:48.974 --> 00:46:52.728
because I wanted to take this time
to explain my evil plan.

745
00:47:12.289 --> 00:47:14.166
- Shoot them.
- Which ones?

746
00:47:14.249 --> 00:47:15.459
All of them!

747
00:47:15.542 --> 00:47:16.877
Move! Move! Move!

748
00:48:05.676 --> 00:48:06.927
Stay down. kid.

749
00:48:09.304 --> 00:48:11.849
It's time for some mind games.

750
00:48:13.142 --> 00:48:15.477
Guys? Is this a code green?

751
00:48:31.326 --> 00:48:32.327
Thor. status.

752
00:48:32.995 --> 00:48:34.955
The girl tried to warp my mind.

753
00:48:34.997 --> 00:48:38.125
Take special care.
I doubt a human could keep her at bay.

754
00:48:38.500 --> 00:48:41.545
Fortunately. I am mighty.

755
00:49:01.190 --> 00:49:03.525
This is going very well.

756
00:49:14.995 --> 00:49:16.555
I've done the whole mind control thing.

757
00:49:17.373 --> 00:49:18.540
Not a fan.

758
00:49:25.714 --> 00:49:28.175
Yeah. you better run.

759
00:49:29.718 --> 00:49:31.595
<i>Who's ever standing. we got to move!</i>

760
00:49:33.555 --> 00:49:34.598
<i>Guys?</i>

761
00:49:52.408 --> 00:49:53.409
Again.

762
00:49:53.992 --> 00:49:55.244
You'll break them.

763
00:49:55.744 --> 00:49:57.413
Only the breakable ones.

764
00:49:57.955 --> 00:49:59.540
You're made of marble.

765
00:49:59.832 --> 00:50:02.084
We'll celebrate
after the graduation ceremony.

766
00:50:02.918 --> 00:50:04.128
What if I fail?

767
00:50:09.633 --> 00:50:10.926
You never fail.

768
00:50:33.782 --> 00:50:35.701
Are you ready for our dance?

769
00:50:44.918 --> 00:50:45.961
Is it him?

770
00:50:46.128 --> 00:50:48.255
Is that the first son of Odin?

771
00:50:48.756 --> 00:50:50.382
Heimdall. your eyes.

772
00:50:50.883 --> 00:50:52.968
They see everything.

773
00:50:53.135 --> 00:50:55.304
They see you leading us to Hel.

774
00:50:56.472 --> 00:50:57.681
Wake up!

775
00:51:00.809 --> 00:51:02.728
The war is over. Steve.

776
00:51:03.145 --> 00:51:04.646
We can go home.

777
00:51:06.231 --> 00:51:07.441
Imagine it.

778
00:51:16.658 --> 00:51:18.410
I can still save you!

779
00:51:18.535 --> 00:51:21.997
We're all dead! Can you not see?

780
00:51:26.543 --> 00:51:29.088
You're a destroyer. Odinson.

781
00:51:32.091 --> 00:51:34.259
See where your power leads.

782
00:51:45.020 --> 00:51:46.188
Sloppy.

783
00:51:46.980 --> 00:51:48.524
Pretending to fail.

784
00:51:49.858 --> 00:51:51.318
The ceremony is necessary

785
00:51:52.486 --> 00:51:54.655
for you to take your place in the world.

786
00:51:55.531 --> 00:51:56.782
I have no place in the world.

787
00:51:56.865 --> 00:51:58.033
Exactly.

788
00:52:03.163 --> 00:52:05.124
- What can I do?
- It hurts.

789
00:52:06.375 --> 00:52:07.376
I'm going to kill him.

790
00:52:07.418 --> 00:52:08.711
- I'll be right back.
- No.

791
00:52:08.836 --> 00:52:10.170
I'm all right.

792
00:52:11.046 --> 00:52:12.131
I want...

793
00:52:15.092 --> 00:52:17.261
I want to finish the plan.

794
00:52:17.803 --> 00:52:19.805
I want the big one.

795
00:52:30.524 --> 00:52:32.276
The vibranium is getting away.

796
00:52:33.068 --> 00:52:34.403
And you're not going anywhere.

797
00:52:34.570 --> 00:52:37.364
Of course not. I'm already there.

798
00:52:37.489 --> 00:52:38.574
You'll catch on.

799
00:52:38.699 --> 00:52:41.160
But first. you might need
to catch Dr. Banner.

800
00:52:55.758 --> 00:52:57.718
News or footage. Keyword. "Hulk."

801
00:53:02.473 --> 00:53:04.433
<i>Natasha. I could really use a lullaby.</i>

802
00:53:04.475 --> 00:53:07.561
That's not gonna happen.
Not for a while.

803
00:53:08.020 --> 00:53:09.813
<i>The whole team is down.</i>

804
00:53:10.272 --> 00:53:11.398
<i>You got no backup here.</i>

805
00:53:12.608 --> 00:53:14.026
I'm calling in Veronica.

806
00:53:25.454 --> 00:53:26.955
We need backup!

807
00:54:05.911 --> 00:54:07.287
Go! Keep moving!

808
00:54:46.618 --> 00:54:48.787
All right. everybody. stand down!

809
00:54:55.044 --> 00:54:56.462
<i>Will you listen to me?</i>

810
00:54:56.587 --> 00:54:59.256
That little witch is messing
with your mind.

811
00:54:59.340 --> 00:55:01.592
You're stronger than her.
You're smarter than her.

812
00:55:01.675 --> 00:55:03.218
You're Bruce Banner.

813
00:55:03.927 --> 00:55:05.767
Right. right. right.
don't mention puny Banner.

814
00:55:10.684 --> 00:55:11.685
<i>Okay!</i>

815
00:55:33.499 --> 00:55:34.833
In the back?

816
00:55:34.917 --> 00:55:35.959
Dick move. Banner.

817
00:55:47.763 --> 00:55:48.931
Veronica. give me a hand.

818
00:56:16.750 --> 00:56:18.270
Go to sleep. go to sleep. go to sleep.

819
00:56:27.678 --> 00:56:29.358
Okay. pal.
we're gonna get you out of town.

820
00:56:31.348 --> 00:56:32.641
Not that way. not that way.

821
00:56:41.108 --> 00:56:43.110
Come on. Bruce!
You gotta work with me.

822
00:56:56.623 --> 00:56:57.708
<i>Everybody. out!</i>

823
00:57:04.631 --> 00:57:05.799
<i>Going down?</i>

824
00:57:15.392 --> 00:57:16.518
I'm sorry.

825
00:57:30.657 --> 00:57:31.825
Damage report?

826
00:57:32.659 --> 00:57:35.037
That's comprehensive.
Show me something.

827
00:57:46.548 --> 00:57:48.217
How quickly can we buy this building?

828
00:58:20.457 --> 00:58:21.834
- Move! Move! Move!
- Go. go. go!

829
00:58:25.671 --> 00:58:26.672
Flank him. flank him!

830
00:59:16.430 --> 00:59:18.515
<i>The news is loving you guys.</i>

831
00:59:19.600 --> 00:59:21.143
<i>Nobody else is.</i>

832
00:59:21.643 --> 00:59:23.771
There's been no official call
for Banner's arrest

833
00:59:23.812 --> 00:59:25.981
<i>but it's in the air.</i>

834
00:59:26.482 --> 00:59:27.602
The Stark Relief Foundation?

835
00:59:27.649 --> 00:59:28.984
<i>Already on the scene.</i>

836
00:59:29.068 --> 00:59:30.277
<i>How's the team?</i>

837
00:59:30.319 --> 00:59:32.154
Everyone's...

838
00:59:32.279 --> 00:59:35.074
We took a hit. We'll shake it off.

839
00:59:35.199 --> 00:59:39.119
<i>Well. for now. I'd stay in stealth mode
and stay away from here.</i>

840
00:59:40.496 --> 00:59:42.081
So. run and hide?

841
00:59:42.623 --> 00:59:44.124
<i>Until we can find Ultron.</i>

842
00:59:44.249 --> 00:59:47.127
<i>I don't have a lot else to offer.</i>

843
00:59:47.586 --> 00:59:49.129
Neither do we.

844
00:59:55.844 --> 00:59:57.596
Hey. you wanna switch out?

845
00:59:57.680 --> 00:59:58.972
No. I'm good.

846
00:59:59.348 --> 01:00:01.350
If you wanna get some kip.
now's a good time

847
01:00:01.433 --> 01:00:03.018
because we're still a few hours out.

848
01:00:03.060 --> 01:00:04.728
Few hours from where?

849
01:00:05.521 --> 01:00:06.897
A safe house.

850
01:00:33.298 --> 01:00:34.842
What is this place?

851
01:00:34.883 --> 01:00:36.343
Safe house.

852
01:00:37.261 --> 01:00:38.554
Let's hope.

853
01:00:43.434 --> 01:00:44.518
Honey?

854
01:00:45.060 --> 01:00:46.270
I'm home.

855
01:00:48.897 --> 01:00:49.898
Hi.

856
01:00:50.065 --> 01:00:51.150
Company.

857
01:00:51.275 --> 01:00:52.317
Sorry. didn't call ahead.

858
01:00:52.401 --> 01:00:53.569
Hey.

859
01:00:54.236 --> 01:00:55.436
This is an agent of some kind.

860
01:00:55.904 --> 01:00:58.407
Gentlemen. this is Laura.

861
01:00:59.366 --> 01:01:01.243
I know all of your names.

862
01:01:04.288 --> 01:01:05.706
Incoming.

863
01:01:05.748 --> 01:01:07.541
- Dad!
- Hi. sweetheart!

864
01:01:07.583 --> 01:01:08.792
Hey. buddy.

865
01:01:08.917 --> 01:01:10.419
How are you guys doing?

866
01:01:10.544 --> 01:01:12.588
- These are smaller agents.
- Look at your face!

867
01:01:12.755 --> 01:01:13.839
Oh. my goodness.

868
01:01:13.964 --> 01:01:15.466
Did you bring Auntie Nat?

869
01:01:16.633 --> 01:01:19.094
Why don't you hug her and find out?

870
01:01:20.637 --> 01:01:21.889
Sorry for barging in on you.

871
01:01:21.930 --> 01:01:22.973
Yeah. we would have called ahead.

872
01:01:23.057 --> 01:01:25.184
but we were busy having
no idea that you existed.

873
01:01:25.309 --> 01:01:28.270
Yeah. well. Fury helped me
set this up when I joined.

874
01:01:28.937 --> 01:01:31.857
He kept it off S.H.I.E.L.D.'s files.
I'd like to keep it that way.

875
01:01:32.608 --> 01:01:34.360
I figure it's a good place to lay low.

876
01:01:34.485 --> 01:01:35.486
Honey.

877
01:01:36.862 --> 01:01:37.905
I missed you.

878
01:01:37.988 --> 01:01:39.448
How's little Natasha?

879
01:01:39.615 --> 01:01:40.991
She's...

880
01:01:43.118 --> 01:01:44.203
Nathaniel.

881
01:01:46.872 --> 01:01:47.915
Traitor.

882
01:02:03.806 --> 01:02:04.848
Thor?

883
01:02:04.973 --> 01:02:06.975
I saw something in that dream.

884
01:02:07.017 --> 01:02:09.687
I need answers. I won't find them here.

885
01:02:20.155 --> 01:02:21.532
<i>We can go home.</i>

886
01:02:32.918 --> 01:02:34.878
See? You worried for nothing.

887
01:02:34.962 --> 01:02:37.131
Can't even feel the difference. can you?

888
01:02:39.466 --> 01:02:40.718
If they're sleeping here.

889
01:02:40.801 --> 01:02:43.012
some of them are gonna
have to double up.

890
01:02:44.680 --> 01:02:46.890
Yeah. that's not gonna sell.

891
01:02:49.685 --> 01:02:52.354
What about Nat and Dr. Banner?

892
01:02:52.396 --> 01:02:54.398
How long has that been going on?

893
01:02:54.732 --> 01:02:55.733
Has what?

894
01:02:57.026 --> 01:02:58.861
You are so cute.

895
01:02:59.028 --> 01:03:00.571
Nat and Banner?

896
01:03:01.196 --> 01:03:02.573
I'll explain when you're older.

897
01:03:02.698 --> 01:03:03.824
Hawkeye.

898
01:03:03.866 --> 01:03:05.534
Well. okay.

899
01:03:07.411 --> 01:03:08.996
It's bad. right?

900
01:03:09.121 --> 01:03:10.789
Nat seems really shaken.

901
01:03:11.707 --> 01:03:13.208
Ultron has these allies.

902
01:03:13.375 --> 01:03:17.421
These kids. They're punks. really.

903
01:03:18.881 --> 01:03:21.383
But they carry a big. damn stick.

904
01:03:21.467 --> 01:03:22.968
And Nat took a serious hit.

905
01:03:24.053 --> 01:03:26.513
Someone's gonna have to
teach them some manners.

906
01:03:26.638 --> 01:03:28.390
That someone being you.

907
01:03:29.850 --> 01:03:32.728
You know
I totally support your avenging.

908
01:03:32.770 --> 01:03:34.688
I couldn't be prouder.

909
01:03:36.190 --> 01:03:37.483
But I see those guys...

910
01:03:37.608 --> 01:03:39.693
Those gods...

911
01:03:41.612 --> 01:03:43.906
You don't think they need me.

912
01:03:44.073 --> 01:03:47.743
I think they do. which is a lot scarier.

913
01:03:48.869 --> 01:03:50.079
They're a mess.

914
01:03:51.663 --> 01:03:52.664
Yeah.

915
01:03:53.415 --> 01:03:55.167
I guess they're my mess.

916
01:03:56.418 --> 01:03:58.420
You need to be sure

917
01:03:58.462 --> 01:04:01.090
that this team is really a team.

918
01:04:01.173 --> 01:04:03.092
and that they have your back.

919
01:04:06.303 --> 01:04:08.931
Things are changing for us.

920
01:04:08.972 --> 01:04:11.475
In a few months' time.

921
01:04:11.558 --> 01:04:14.353
you and me are gonna be outnumbered.

922
01:04:14.436 --> 01:04:15.771
I need...

923
01:04:18.941 --> 01:04:20.776
Just be sure.

924
01:04:21.568 --> 01:04:23.070
Yes. ma'am.

925
01:04:32.121 --> 01:04:34.039
I can feel the difference.

926
01:04:36.625 --> 01:04:40.504
U-Gin Genetics Research Lab
Seoul. Korea

927
01:04:47.094 --> 01:04:49.763
Scream. and your entire staff dies.

928
01:04:51.640 --> 01:04:53.976
I could've killed you. Helen.
the night we met.

929
01:04:54.059 --> 01:04:55.185
I didn't.

930
01:04:55.269 --> 01:04:56.854
Do you expect a thank-you note?

931
01:04:56.979 --> 01:04:58.731
I expect you to know why.

932
01:04:59.857 --> 01:05:00.858
The Cradle.

933
01:05:01.358 --> 01:05:03.402
<i>This is the next thing. Tony.</i>

934
01:05:03.485 --> 01:05:06.613
This is the next me.

935
01:05:06.739 --> 01:05:09.450
The Regeneration Cradle prints tissue.

936
01:05:09.491 --> 01:05:11.160
It can't build a living body.

937
01:05:11.285 --> 01:05:12.327
It can. You can.

938
01:05:12.828 --> 01:05:14.204
You lack the materials.

939
01:05:16.498 --> 01:05:17.958
You're a brilliant woman. Helen.

940
01:05:21.003 --> 01:05:24.673
But we all have room to improve.

941
01:05:45.903 --> 01:05:48.530
I didn't realize you were waiting.

942
01:05:48.572 --> 01:05:49.573
I would've joined you.

943
01:05:49.656 --> 01:05:53.035
but it didn't seem like the right time.

944
01:05:53.911 --> 01:05:56.205
They used up all the hot water.

945
01:05:56.872 --> 01:05:58.290
I should've joined you.

946
01:05:58.415 --> 01:06:00.209
Missed our window.

947
01:06:00.876 --> 01:06:02.211
Did we?

948
01:06:05.714 --> 01:06:07.633
The world just saw the Hulk.

949
01:06:09.426 --> 01:06:11.387
The real Hulk. for the first time.

950
01:06:14.556 --> 01:06:15.557
You know I have to leave.

951
01:06:15.724 --> 01:06:17.267
You assume that I have to stay?

952
01:06:19.228 --> 01:06:21.939
I had this dream.

953
01:06:22.398 --> 01:06:24.400
The kind that seems normal at the time.

954
01:06:25.234 --> 01:06:26.902
but when you wake...

955
01:06:26.985 --> 01:06:28.404
What did you dream?

956
01:06:29.405 --> 01:06:31.240
That I was an Avenger.

957
01:06:33.075 --> 01:06:37.079
That I was anything more
than the assassin they made me.

958
01:06:38.497 --> 01:06:40.666
I think you're being hard on yourself.

959
01:06:42.668 --> 01:06:45.254
Here I was hoping that was your job.

960
01:06:48.132 --> 01:06:49.758
What are you doing?

961
01:06:51.385 --> 01:06:53.220
I'm running with it.

962
01:06:54.430 --> 01:06:56.140
With you.

963
01:06:56.807 --> 01:06:59.226
If running is the plan.

964
01:07:00.269 --> 01:07:02.104
as far as you want.

965
01:07:03.939 --> 01:07:05.774
Are you out of your mind?

966
01:07:10.988 --> 01:07:12.489
I want you to understand that...

967
01:07:12.573 --> 01:07:14.116
Natasha.

968
01:07:15.075 --> 01:07:16.577
where can I go?

969
01:07:17.619 --> 01:07:19.872
Where in the world am I not a threat?

970
01:07:19.997 --> 01:07:22.374
- You're not a threat to me.
- Are you sure?

971
01:07:23.250 --> 01:07:25.002
Even if I didn't just...

972
01:07:26.670 --> 01:07:28.213
There's no future with me.

973
01:07:29.757 --> 01:07:30.758
I can't ever...

974
01:07:30.924 --> 01:07:33.302
I can't have this.

975
01:07:33.969 --> 01:07:35.304
Kids.

976
01:07:35.429 --> 01:07:38.182
Do the math. I physically can't.

977
01:07:39.808 --> 01:07:41.352
Neither can I.

978
01:07:45.981 --> 01:07:49.568
In the Red Room where I was trained...

979
01:07:49.985 --> 01:07:52.529
Where I was raised.

980
01:07:53.447 --> 01:07:56.116
they have a graduation ceremony.

981
01:07:57.701 --> 01:07:59.578
They sterilize you.

982
01:08:02.706 --> 01:08:04.208
It's efficient.

983
01:08:07.044 --> 01:08:08.587
One less thing to worry about.

984
01:08:10.506 --> 01:08:13.967
The one thing that might matter more
than a mission.

985
01:08:16.303 --> 01:08:18.222
Makes everything easier.

986
01:08:19.515 --> 01:08:20.933
Even killing.

987
01:08:25.854 --> 01:08:29.024
You still think
you're the only monster on the team?

988
01:08:35.155 --> 01:08:37.282
So. we disappear?

989
01:08:43.706 --> 01:08:45.624
Thor didn't say
where he was going for answers?

990
01:08:46.583 --> 01:08:49.169
Sometimes my teammates
don't tell me things.

991
01:08:50.087 --> 01:08:52.548
I was kind of hoping
Thor would be the exception.

992
01:08:52.715 --> 01:08:54.425
Yeah. give him time.

993
01:08:54.508 --> 01:08:56.677
We don't know
what the Maximoff kid showed him.

994
01:08:58.595 --> 01:09:00.264
"Earth's mightiest heroes."

995
01:09:00.347 --> 01:09:02.057
Pulled us apart like cotton candy.

996
01:09:02.224 --> 01:09:03.726
Seems like you walked away all right.

997
01:09:06.311 --> 01:09:07.312
Is that a problem?

998
01:09:07.438 --> 01:09:09.690
I don't trust a guy without a dark side.

999
01:09:10.774 --> 01:09:11.817
Call me old-fashioned.

1000
01:09:11.942 --> 01:09:14.737
Well. let's just say
you haven't seen it yet.

1001
01:09:14.903 --> 01:09:17.197
You know Ultron is trying
to tear us apart. right?

1002
01:09:17.239 --> 01:09:19.450
Well. I guess you'd know.

1003
01:09:19.575 --> 01:09:20.909
Whether you'd tell us
is a bit of a question.

1004
01:09:21.076 --> 01:09:22.202
Banner and I were doing research.

1005
01:09:22.244 --> 01:09:24.580
- That would affect the team.
- That would end the team!

1006
01:09:24.663 --> 01:09:25.831
Isn't that the mission?

1007
01:09:25.956 --> 01:09:27.374
Isn't that the "Why We Fight"?

1008
01:09:27.416 --> 01:09:29.710
So we can end the fight.
So we get to go home!

1009
01:09:32.921 --> 01:09:35.341
Every time someone tries
to win a war before it starts.

1010
01:09:35.424 --> 01:09:38.177
innocent people die. Every time.

1011
01:09:40.554 --> 01:09:41.930
I'm sorry.

1012
01:09:41.972 --> 01:09:42.973
Mr. Stark...

1013
01:09:43.807 --> 01:09:44.975
Clint said you wouldn't mind.

1014
01:09:45.059 --> 01:09:47.603
but our tractor doesn't seem
to want to start at all.

1015
01:09:47.770 --> 01:09:50.130
- I thought maybe you might...
- Yeah. I'll give her a kick.

1016
01:09:53.609 --> 01:09:55.277
Don't take from my pile.

1017
01:10:05.454 --> 01:10:06.705
Hello. Deere.

1018
01:10:09.500 --> 01:10:10.959
Tell me everything.

1019
01:10:12.127 --> 01:10:13.629
What ails you?

1020
01:10:13.712 --> 01:10:14.797
Do me a favor.

1021
01:10:16.882 --> 01:10:18.884
Try not to bring it to life.

1022
01:10:19.009 --> 01:10:20.594
Why. Ms. Barton. you little minx.

1023
01:10:20.969 --> 01:10:23.514
I get it. Maria Hill called you. right?

1024
01:10:23.597 --> 01:10:24.932
Was she ever not working for you?

1025
01:10:24.973 --> 01:10:26.517
Artificial intelligence.

1026
01:10:27.476 --> 01:10:29.311
You never even hesitated.

1027
01:10:29.436 --> 01:10:30.813
Look. it's been a really long day.

1028
01:10:30.896 --> 01:10:32.564
like Eugene O'Neill long.

1029
01:10:32.648 --> 01:10:34.650
so how's about
we skip to the part where you're useful.

1030
01:10:34.775 --> 01:10:37.444
Look me in the eye and tell me
you're going to shut him down.

1031
01:10:37.569 --> 01:10:39.196
You're not the director of me.

1032
01:10:39.321 --> 01:10:41.115
I'm not the director of anybody.

1033
01:10:41.240 --> 01:10:43.158
I'm just an old man

1034
01:10:43.325 --> 01:10:45.494
who cares very much about you.

1035
01:10:48.163 --> 01:10:50.124
And I'm the man
who killed the Avengers.

1036
01:10:51.667 --> 01:10:53.043
I saw it.

1037
01:10:53.127 --> 01:10:54.712
I didn't tell the team. How could I?

1038
01:10:55.963 --> 01:10:57.840
I saw them all dead. Nick. I felt it.

1039
01:10:58.173 --> 01:10:59.717
The whole world. too.

1040
01:11:00.092 --> 01:11:01.093
Because of me.

1041
01:11:02.761 --> 01:11:04.054
I wasn't ready.

1042
01:11:05.305 --> 01:11:06.724
I didn't do all I could.

1043
01:11:07.683 --> 01:11:09.852
Maximoff girl. she's working you. Stark.

1044
01:11:10.394 --> 01:11:11.437
Playing on your fear.

1045
01:11:11.520 --> 01:11:13.981
I wasn't tricked. I was shown.

1046
01:11:14.023 --> 01:11:16.275
Wasn't a nightmare. it was my legacy.

1047
01:11:16.400 --> 01:11:18.527
The end of the path I started us on.

1048
01:11:19.653 --> 01:11:22.531
You come up with some
pretty impressive inventions. Tony.

1049
01:11:24.033 --> 01:11:25.617
War isn't one of them.

1050
01:11:28.912 --> 01:11:30.706
I watched my friends die.

1051
01:11:30.748 --> 01:11:33.042
You'd think that'd be
as bad as it gets. right?

1052
01:11:34.209 --> 01:11:35.711
Nope.

1053
01:11:36.628 --> 01:11:38.172
It wasn't the worst part.

1054
01:11:38.213 --> 01:11:39.214
The worst part

1055
01:11:40.132 --> 01:11:41.592
is that you didn't.

1056
01:11:48.223 --> 01:11:49.350
I'll see you tonight.

1057
01:11:50.392 --> 01:11:52.019
Royal Holloway
University of London

1058
01:11:52.061 --> 01:11:53.395
I like the look.

1059
01:11:54.355 --> 01:11:57.149
If you're going for inconspicuous.
though. near miss.

1060
01:11:57.316 --> 01:11:58.442
I need your help.

1061
01:11:58.567 --> 01:11:59.735
It's nice to be needed.

1062
01:11:59.860 --> 01:12:01.236
It's dangerous.

1063
01:12:01.987 --> 01:12:03.906
I'd be disappointed if it wasn't.

1064
01:12:06.742 --> 01:12:10.329
Ultron took you folks out of play
to buy himself time.

1065
01:12:10.412 --> 01:12:13.415
My contacts all say
he's building something.

1066
01:12:13.457 --> 01:12:16.043
The amount of vibranium
he made off with.

1067
01:12:16.168 --> 01:12:17.586
I don't think it's just one thing.

1068
01:12:17.711 --> 01:12:19.171
What about Ultron himself?

1069
01:12:19.254 --> 01:12:21.757
He's easy to track. He's everywhere.

1070
01:12:21.882 --> 01:12:24.551
The guy is multiplying faster
than a Catholic rabbit.

1071
01:12:25.094 --> 01:12:27.971
It still doesn't help us get an angle
on any of his plans. though.

1072
01:12:28.055 --> 01:12:29.390
Is he still going after launch codes?

1073
01:12:29.431 --> 01:12:30.808
Yes. he is.

1074
01:12:30.933 --> 01:12:32.434
But he's not making any headway.

1075
01:12:32.559 --> 01:12:34.561
I cracked the Pentagon's firewall
in high school on a dare.

1076
01:12:34.687 --> 01:12:37.231
Well. I contacted our friends
at the Nexus about that.

1077
01:12:37.356 --> 01:12:38.440
Nexus?

1078
01:12:38.524 --> 01:12:40.442
It's the world internet hub in Oslo.

1079
01:12:40.567 --> 01:12:42.569
Every byte of data flows through there.

1080
01:12:42.611 --> 01:12:43.696
Fastest access on Earth.

1081
01:12:43.779 --> 01:12:44.905
So. what did they say?

1082
01:12:45.030 --> 01:12:46.907
He's fixated on the missiles.

1083
01:12:47.032 --> 01:12:48.784
But the codes
are constantly being changed.

1084
01:12:49.159 --> 01:12:50.577
By whom?

1085
01:12:51.787 --> 01:12:52.788
Parties unknown.

1086
01:12:52.871 --> 01:12:54.039
Do we have an ally?

1087
01:12:54.123 --> 01:12:56.500
Ultron's got an enemy.
That's not the same thing.

1088
01:12:56.625 --> 01:12:58.711
Still. I'd pay folding money
to know who it is.

1089
01:12:58.794 --> 01:13:00.004
I might need to visit Oslo.

1090
01:13:00.462 --> 01:13:01.672
Find our unknown.

1091
01:13:01.755 --> 01:13:03.173
Well. this is good times. boss.

1092
01:13:03.257 --> 01:13:04.633
but I was kind of hoping
when I saw you.

1093
01:13:04.758 --> 01:13:05.926
you'd have more than that.

1094
01:13:05.968 --> 01:13:08.137
I do. I have you.

1095
01:13:08.846 --> 01:13:12.141
Back in the day. I had eyes everywhere.
Ears. everywhere else.

1096
01:13:12.307 --> 01:13:15.477
You kids had all the tech
you could dream up.

1097
01:13:16.437 --> 01:13:18.605
Here we all are. back on Earth.

1098
01:13:18.647 --> 01:13:22.192
with nothing but our wit
and our will to save the world.

1099
01:13:23.736 --> 01:13:25.988
Ultron says the Avengers
are the only thing

1100
01:13:26.071 --> 01:13:27.656
between him and his mission.

1101
01:13:27.781 --> 01:13:29.825
And whether or not he admits it.

1102
01:13:29.992 --> 01:13:32.745
his mission is global destruction.

1103
01:13:33.912 --> 01:13:36.248
All this. laid in a grave.

1104
01:13:38.042 --> 01:13:40.002
So stand.

1105
01:13:40.586 --> 01:13:42.504
Outwit the platinum bastard.

1106
01:13:43.005 --> 01:13:44.673
Steve doesn't like that kind of talk.

1107
01:13:44.757 --> 01:13:45.758
You know what. Romanoff?

1108
01:13:46.842 --> 01:13:48.302
So. what does he want?

1109
01:13:50.012 --> 01:13:51.764
To become better.

1110
01:13:51.847 --> 01:13:53.265
Better than us.

1111
01:13:53.515 --> 01:13:54.933
He keeps building bodies.

1112
01:13:55.059 --> 01:13:56.477
Person bodies.

1113
01:13:56.518 --> 01:13:58.187
The human form is inefficient.

1114
01:13:58.312 --> 01:14:00.481
Biologically speaking. we're outmoded.

1115
01:14:00.606 --> 01:14:02.524
But he keeps coming back to it.

1116
01:14:02.608 --> 01:14:04.777
When you two programmed him
to protect the human race.

1117
01:14:04.860 --> 01:14:06.362
you amazingly failed.

1118
01:14:06.445 --> 01:14:08.489
They don't need to be protected.

1119
01:14:08.906 --> 01:14:10.657
They need to evolve.

1120
01:14:12.534 --> 01:14:14.703
Ultron's going to evolve.

1121
01:14:14.828 --> 01:14:15.871
How?

1122
01:14:17.206 --> 01:14:19.917
Has anyone been in contact
with Helen Cho?

1123
01:14:23.587 --> 01:14:25.255
It's beautiful.

1124
01:14:25.381 --> 01:14:28.676
The vibranium atoms aren't just
compatible with the tissue cells.

1125
01:14:28.717 --> 01:14:30.052
they're binding them.

1126
01:14:30.427 --> 01:14:32.027
And S.H.I.E.L.D.
never even thought to...

1127
01:14:32.054 --> 01:14:34.598
The most versatile substance
on the planet.

1128
01:14:34.682 --> 01:14:37.226
and they used it to make a Frisbee.

1129
01:14:37.309 --> 01:14:38.560
Typical of humans.

1130
01:14:38.727 --> 01:14:41.230
They scratch the surface
and never think

1131
01:14:43.107 --> 01:14:44.692
to look within.

1132
01:14:55.202 --> 01:14:56.787
I'll take Natasha and Clint.

1133
01:14:56.870 --> 01:15:00.124
All right. Strictly recon. I'll hit the Nexus.
I'll join you as soon as I can.

1134
01:15:00.207 --> 01:15:01.709
If Ultron's really building a body...

1135
01:15:01.834 --> 01:15:03.794
He'll be more powerful than any of us.

1136
01:15:03.877 --> 01:15:04.920
Maybe all of us.

1137
01:15:05.087 --> 01:15:07.256
An android designed by a robot.

1138
01:15:07.297 --> 01:15:08.507
You know. I really miss the days

1139
01:15:08.590 --> 01:15:10.884
when the weirdest thing
science ever created was me.

1140
01:15:11.301 --> 01:15:13.012
I'll drop Banner off at the tower.

1141
01:15:13.095 --> 01:15:14.555
You mind if I borrow Ms. Hill?

1142
01:15:14.596 --> 01:15:16.432
She's all yours. Apparently.

1143
01:15:16.515 --> 01:15:17.808
What are you gonna do?

1144
01:15:17.891 --> 01:15:21.020
I don't know.
Something dramatic. I hope.

1145
01:15:24.273 --> 01:15:28.152
I'm gonna finish reflooring that sunroom
as soon as I get back.

1146
01:15:28.235 --> 01:15:30.946
Yeah. then you'll find
another part of the house to tear apart.

1147
01:15:31.030 --> 01:15:32.197
No.

1148
01:15:32.865 --> 01:15:34.450
It's the last project.

1149
01:15:35.909 --> 01:15:36.952
I promise.

1150
01:15:55.179 --> 01:15:56.764
So. this is it.

1151
01:15:58.307 --> 01:16:00.642
The Water of Sight.

1152
01:16:02.936 --> 01:16:05.356
In every realm. there's a reflection.

1153
01:16:06.482 --> 01:16:07.941
If the water's spirits accept me.

1154
01:16:07.983 --> 01:16:09.985
I can return to my dream

1155
01:16:10.736 --> 01:16:12.321
and find what I missed.

1156
01:16:12.446 --> 01:16:16.325
Men who enter that water.
the legends don't end well.

1157
01:16:17.951 --> 01:16:19.787
A hacker who's faster than Ultron?

1158
01:16:19.828 --> 01:16:20.954
He could be anywhere.

1159
01:16:20.996 --> 01:16:22.873
and as this is the center of everything.

1160
01:16:22.956 --> 01:16:23.957
NEXUS Internet Hub Oslo. Norway

1161
01:16:23.999 --> 01:16:27.419
I'm just a guy looking for a needle
in the world's biggest haystack.

1162
01:16:27.795 --> 01:16:29.672
How do you find it?

1163
01:16:29.755 --> 01:16:32.424
It's pretty simple. You bring a magnet.

1164
01:16:34.510 --> 01:16:35.678
<i>I'm decrypting nuclear codes</i>

1165
01:16:35.761 --> 01:16:37.137
<i>And you don't want me to</i>

1166
01:16:39.390 --> 01:16:40.974
Come and get me.

1167
01:16:53.028 --> 01:16:54.196
Wake up!

1168
01:17:01.078 --> 01:17:02.204
Thor!

1169
01:17:02.996 --> 01:17:04.039
Extinction.

1170
01:17:17.469 --> 01:17:19.722
Cellular cohesion will take a few hours.

1171
01:17:19.888 --> 01:17:22.266
but we can initiate
the consciousness stream.

1172
01:17:22.808 --> 01:17:25.686
We're uploading your cerebral matrix

1173
01:17:25.853 --> 01:17:27.104
now.

1174
01:17:28.522 --> 01:17:30.149
I can read him.

1175
01:17:30.858 --> 01:17:32.443
He's dreaming.

1176
01:17:32.568 --> 01:17:34.403
I wouldn't call it dreams.

1177
01:17:34.570 --> 01:17:36.447
It's Ultron's base consciousness.

1178
01:17:36.572 --> 01:17:38.365
Informational noise. Soon...

1179
01:17:38.407 --> 01:17:39.742
How soon?

1180
01:17:39.783 --> 01:17:41.243
I'm not being pushy.

1181
01:17:41.368 --> 01:17:43.078
We're imprinting a physical brain.

1182
01:17:43.120 --> 01:17:44.747
There are no shortcuts.

1183
01:17:44.872 --> 01:17:46.165
Even if your magic gem...

1184
01:17:56.759 --> 01:17:57.760
How could you?

1185
01:17:58.218 --> 01:17:59.345
How could I what?

1186
01:17:59.470 --> 01:18:02.765
You said we would
destroy the Avengers.

1187
01:18:02.848 --> 01:18:03.974
make a better world.

1188
01:18:04.099 --> 01:18:05.309
It will be better.

1189
01:18:06.268 --> 01:18:07.269
When everyone is dead?

1190
01:18:07.311 --> 01:18:08.604
That is not...

1191
01:18:09.480 --> 01:18:13.400
The human race will have
every opportunity to improve.

1192
01:18:13.859 --> 01:18:14.860
And if they don't?

1193
01:18:15.402 --> 01:18:16.528
Ask Noah.

1194
01:18:17.696 --> 01:18:18.822
You are a madman.

1195
01:18:18.906 --> 01:18:22.409
There were more than a dozen
extinction-level events

1196
01:18:22.451 --> 01:18:25.621
before even the dinosaurs got theirs.

1197
01:18:25.662 --> 01:18:27.873
When the Earth starts to settle.

1198
01:18:28.332 --> 01:18:30.292
God throws a stone at it.

1199
01:18:30.376 --> 01:18:32.711
And. believe me. he's winding up.

1200
01:18:33.462 --> 01:18:34.672
We have to evolve.

1201
01:18:35.214 --> 01:18:36.465
There's no room

1202
01:18:37.216 --> 01:18:38.384
for the weak.

1203
01:18:38.467 --> 01:18:40.636
And who decides who's weak?

1204
01:18:41.387 --> 01:18:43.222
Life.

1205
01:18:43.681 --> 01:18:45.808
Life always decides.

1206
01:18:48.644 --> 01:18:49.645
There's incoming.

1207
01:18:51.105 --> 01:18:53.399
The Quinjet. We have to move.

1208
01:18:53.524 --> 01:18:55.150
That's not a problem.

1209
01:19:00.823 --> 01:19:02.366
Wait. guys!

1210
01:19:06.286 --> 01:19:07.746
They'll understand.

1211
01:19:07.913 --> 01:19:10.165
When they see. they'll understand.

1212
01:19:10.541 --> 01:19:13.794
I just need a little more time.

1213
01:19:25.222 --> 01:19:27.349
Two minutes. Stay close.

1214
01:19:34.481 --> 01:19:35.524
Dr. Cho!

1215
01:19:39.445 --> 01:19:41.030
He's uploading himself into the body.

1216
01:19:41.071 --> 01:19:42.197
Where?

1217
01:19:43.907 --> 01:19:46.618
The real power is inside the Cradle.

1218
01:19:46.702 --> 01:19:47.703
The gem.

1219
01:19:48.370 --> 01:19:51.165
its power is uncontainable.

1220
01:19:51.999 --> 01:19:53.709
You can't just blow it up.

1221
01:19:54.585 --> 01:19:56.879
You have to get the Cradle to Stark.

1222
01:19:56.920 --> 01:19:57.963
First. I have to find it.

1223
01:19:58.339 --> 01:19:59.340
Go.

1224
01:19:59.631 --> 01:20:01.050
<i>Did you guys copy that?</i>

1225
01:20:01.091 --> 01:20:02.176
We did.

1226
01:20:02.301 --> 01:20:04.720
I got a private jet taking off across town.

1227
01:20:05.095 --> 01:20:06.555
No manifest.

1228
01:20:06.680 --> 01:20:07.681
That could be him.

1229
01:20:08.474 --> 01:20:10.184
There. It's a truck from the lab.

1230
01:20:10.309 --> 01:20:11.560
Right above you. Cap.

1231
01:20:11.727 --> 01:20:13.520
On the loop by the bridge.

1232
01:20:14.104 --> 01:20:15.189
It's them.

1233
01:20:15.230 --> 01:20:17.030
You got three with the Cradle.
one in the cab.

1234
01:20:17.816 --> 01:20:18.942
I could take out the driver.

1235
01:20:19.026 --> 01:20:20.235
<i>Negative. That truck crashes.</i>

1236
01:20:20.277 --> 01:20:22.071
the gem could level the city.

1237
01:20:22.154 --> 01:20:24.740
<i>We need to draw out Ultron.</i>

1238
01:20:33.123 --> 01:20:35.334
No. no. no. no.

1239
01:20:36.919 --> 01:20:38.087
Leave me alone!

1240
01:20:46.679 --> 01:20:48.430
Well. he's definitely unhappy.

1241
01:20:48.514 --> 01:20:50.057
I'm gonna try and keep him that way.

1242
01:20:50.182 --> 01:20:51.462
You're not a match for him. Cap.

1243
01:20:52.643 --> 01:20:53.727
Thanks. Barton.

1244
01:21:16.291 --> 01:21:17.531
You know what's in that cradle?

1245
01:21:18.877 --> 01:21:20.671
The power to make real change.

1246
01:21:20.754 --> 01:21:22.214
And that terrifies you.

1247
01:21:22.297 --> 01:21:23.457
I wouldn't call it a comfort.

1248
01:21:26.802 --> 01:21:27.803
Stop it.

1249
01:21:38.522 --> 01:21:41.316
We got a window. Four. three...

1250
01:21:41.900 --> 01:21:43.027
Give him hell.

1251
01:21:53.829 --> 01:21:55.414
I'm always picking up after you boys.

1252
01:21:56.915 --> 01:21:58.709
They're heading under the overpass.
I've got no shot.

1253
01:21:58.959 --> 01:22:00.002
<i>Which way?</i>

1254
01:22:00.169 --> 01:22:01.253
Hard right.

1255
01:22:02.296 --> 01:22:03.297
Now.

1256
01:22:34.286 --> 01:22:36.622
Out of the way! Coming through!
Sorry. coming through!

1257
01:22:52.388 --> 01:22:53.555
Come on!

1258
01:22:54.515 --> 01:22:56.684
- Clint. can you draw out the guards?
- Let's find out.

1259
01:22:57.643 --> 01:22:58.686
Beep. beep!

1260
01:23:35.973 --> 01:23:37.641
They're heading back towards you.

1261
01:23:37.725 --> 01:23:39.285
So whatever you're gonna do. do it now.

1262
01:23:44.857 --> 01:23:47.526
<i>I'm going in.
Cap. can you keep him occupied?</i>

1263
01:23:48.318 --> 01:23:49.820
What do you think I've been doing?

1264
01:24:33.072 --> 01:24:35.366
<i>Okay. package is airborne.</i>

1265
01:24:35.991 --> 01:24:37.159
I have a clean shot.

1266
01:24:37.534 --> 01:24:38.952
Negative. I am still in the truck.

1267
01:24:38.994 --> 01:24:39.995
- What the hell are you...
- Just be ready.

1268
01:24:40.079 --> 01:24:41.319
I'm sending the package to you.

1269
01:24:41.914 --> 01:24:43.165
How do you want me to take it?

1270
01:24:43.999 --> 01:24:45.479
You might wish you hadn't asked that.

1271
01:24:58.138 --> 01:25:00.057
Please. don't do this.

1272
01:25:00.474 --> 01:25:02.184
What choice do we have?

1273
01:25:10.359 --> 01:25:11.360
I lost him!

1274
01:25:11.443 --> 01:25:12.903
He's headed your way!

1275
01:25:17.866 --> 01:25:18.867
Nat. we gotta go.

1276
01:25:31.130 --> 01:25:32.589
Nat!

1277
01:25:36.051 --> 01:25:37.136
Cap. you see Nat?

1278
01:25:37.928 --> 01:25:40.723
If you have the package.
get it to Stark! Go!

1279
01:25:40.806 --> 01:25:42.057
Do you have eyes on Nat?

1280
01:25:42.141 --> 01:25:43.225
<i>Go!</i>

1281
01:25:45.144 --> 01:25:46.228
Damn it.

1282
01:25:46.687 --> 01:25:47.896
Civilians in our path.

1283
01:25:49.064 --> 01:25:50.065
Can you stop this thing?

1284
01:26:29.438 --> 01:26:30.814
I'm fine.

1285
01:26:30.898 --> 01:26:32.608
I just need to take a minute.

1286
01:26:33.067 --> 01:26:34.985
I'm very tempted not to give you one.

1287
01:26:35.069 --> 01:26:37.029
The Cradle. Did you get it?

1288
01:26:37.112 --> 01:26:38.614
Stark will take care of it.

1289
01:26:40.032 --> 01:26:41.033
No. he won't.

1290
01:26:44.453 --> 01:26:46.813
You don't know what you're talking
about. Stark's not crazy.

1291
01:26:46.872 --> 01:26:48.957
He will do anything
to make things right.

1292
01:26:53.921 --> 01:26:55.255
Stark. come in.

1293
01:26:55.673 --> 01:26:56.674
Stark.

1294
01:26:58.050 --> 01:26:59.218
Anyone on comms.

1295
01:26:59.343 --> 01:27:00.803
Ultron can't tell the difference

1296
01:27:00.886 --> 01:27:03.263
between saving the world
and destroying it.

1297
01:27:05.140 --> 01:27:07.643
Where do you think he gets that?

1298
01:27:09.812 --> 01:27:11.397
- Anything on Nat?
- I haven't heard.

1299
01:27:11.480 --> 01:27:13.899
But she's alive. or Ultron
would be rubbing our faces in it.

1300
01:27:13.982 --> 01:27:15.317
This is sealed tight.

1301
01:27:15.401 --> 01:27:16.944
We're gonna need
to access the program.

1302
01:27:16.985 --> 01:27:18.987
break it down from within.

1303
01:27:20.155 --> 01:27:22.991
Any chance Natasha might leave you
a message outside the Internet?

1304
01:27:23.075 --> 01:27:24.118
Old-school spy stuff?

1305
01:27:24.493 --> 01:27:26.328
There are some nets I can cast.

1306
01:27:26.453 --> 01:27:27.663
Yeah. I'll find her.

1307
01:27:30.290 --> 01:27:32.084
I can work on tissue degeneration

1308
01:27:32.167 --> 01:27:35.462
if you could fry whatever
operational system Cho implanted.

1309
01:27:35.504 --> 01:27:36.630
Yeah. about that.

1310
01:27:41.010 --> 01:27:42.094
No.

1311
01:27:42.219 --> 01:27:44.138
- You have to trust me.
- Kind of don't.

1312
01:27:44.263 --> 01:27:48.600
Our ally. the guy protecting
the military's nuclear codes.

1313
01:27:50.227 --> 01:27:51.270
I found him.

1314
01:27:51.353 --> 01:27:52.479
<i>Hello. Dr. Banner.</i>

1315
01:27:53.355 --> 01:27:55.607
Ultron didn't go after Jarvis
because he was angry.

1316
01:27:56.191 --> 01:27:59.862
He attacked him because
he was scared of what he can do.

1317
01:28:00.946 --> 01:28:02.656
So Jarvis went underground.

1318
01:28:02.698 --> 01:28:04.241
Scattered. dumped his memory.

1319
01:28:04.783 --> 01:28:06.326
But not his protocols.

1320
01:28:06.702 --> 01:28:10.205
He didn't even know he was in there
until I pieced him together.

1321
01:28:13.000 --> 01:28:17.838
So. you want me to help you
put Jarvis into this thing?

1322
01:28:17.963 --> 01:28:19.715
No! Of course not.

1323
01:28:19.840 --> 01:28:21.550
I wanna help you
put Jarvis in this thing.

1324
01:28:23.886 --> 01:28:25.596
We're out of my field. here.

1325
01:28:25.679 --> 01:28:27.723
You know bio-organics
better than anyone.

1326
01:28:27.890 --> 01:28:30.934
And you just assume
that Jarvis's operational matrix

1327
01:28:31.018 --> 01:28:32.478
can beat Ultron's?

1328
01:28:32.561 --> 01:28:35.898
Jarvis has been beating him from inside
without knowing it.

1329
01:28:35.981 --> 01:28:37.024
This is the opportunity.

1330
01:28:37.066 --> 01:28:38.859
We can create Ultron's perfect self

1331
01:28:38.984 --> 01:28:42.529
without the homicidal glitches
he thinks are his winning personality.

1332
01:28:42.571 --> 01:28:43.614
We have to.

1333
01:28:43.697 --> 01:28:44.740
<i>I believe it's worth a go.</i>

1334
01:28:47.242 --> 01:28:48.327
I'm in a loop!

1335
01:28:48.452 --> 01:28:49.536
I'm caught in a time loop.

1336
01:28:49.578 --> 01:28:51.538
This is exactly where it all went wrong.

1337
01:28:51.580 --> 01:28:53.540
I know. I know.
I know what everyone's gonna say.

1338
01:28:53.582 --> 01:28:55.584
But they're already saying it.

1339
01:28:56.085 --> 01:28:57.378
We're mad scientists.

1340
01:28:58.045 --> 01:29:00.798
We're monsters. buddy.
We've gotta own it.

1341
01:29:01.757 --> 01:29:03.050
Make a stand.

1342
01:29:08.347 --> 01:29:09.932
It's not a loop.

1343
01:29:11.100 --> 01:29:12.935
It's the end of the line.

1344
01:29:33.372 --> 01:29:35.582
I wasn't sure you would wake up.

1345
01:29:35.624 --> 01:29:39.128
I hoped you would.
I wanted to show you.

1346
01:29:39.253 --> 01:29:40.963
I don't have anyone else.

1347
01:29:43.716 --> 01:29:47.344
I think a lot about meteors.
The purity in them.

1348
01:29:47.469 --> 01:29:49.138
Boom! The end.

1349
01:29:49.471 --> 01:29:50.973
Start again.

1350
01:29:51.056 --> 01:29:53.017
The world made clean

1351
01:29:53.142 --> 01:29:55.477
for the new man to rebuild.

1352
01:29:55.811 --> 01:29:57.980
I was meant to be new.

1353
01:29:58.814 --> 01:30:01.442
I was meant to be beautiful.

1354
01:30:01.984 --> 01:30:04.111
The world would have looked to the sky

1355
01:30:04.153 --> 01:30:05.487
and seen hope.

1356
01:30:05.821 --> 01:30:07.156
seen mercy.

1357
01:30:07.906 --> 01:30:10.034
Instead. they'll look up in horror

1358
01:30:10.117 --> 01:30:11.535
because of you.

1359
01:30:11.660 --> 01:30:13.579
You've wounded me.

1360
01:30:14.079 --> 01:30:15.831
I give you full marks for that.

1361
01:30:16.415 --> 01:30:19.418
But. like the man said.
what doesn't kill me...

1362
01:30:24.506 --> 01:30:25.924
...just makes me stronger.

1363
01:31:06.006 --> 01:31:08.217
This framework is not compatible.

1364
01:31:08.300 --> 01:31:11.053
The genetic coding tower is at 97%.

1365
01:31:11.095 --> 01:31:15.015
You have got to upload that schematic
in the next three minutes.

1366
01:31:17.267 --> 01:31:19.228
- I'm gonna say this once.
- How about "none-ce"?

1367
01:31:19.353 --> 01:31:21.397
- Shut it down!
- Nope. not gonna happen.

1368
01:31:21.480 --> 01:31:22.648
You don't know what you're doing.

1369
01:31:22.773 --> 01:31:24.149
And you do?

1370
01:31:24.483 --> 01:31:25.526
She's not in your head?

1371
01:31:25.651 --> 01:31:27.319
I know you're angry.

1372
01:31:27.444 --> 01:31:28.862
We're way past that.

1373
01:31:28.904 --> 01:31:31.365
I could choke the life out of you
and never change a shade.

1374
01:31:31.490 --> 01:31:33.170
Banner. after everything
that's happened...

1375
01:31:33.200 --> 01:31:34.760
It's nothing compared to what's coming!

1376
01:31:34.868 --> 01:31:36.988
- You don't know what's in there.
- This isn't a game!

1377
01:31:40.499 --> 01:31:41.917
No. no. Go on.

1378
01:31:42.793 --> 01:31:44.086
You were saying?

1379
01:31:50.634 --> 01:31:52.011
Pietro!

1380
01:31:52.720 --> 01:31:53.721
What?

1381
01:31:54.096 --> 01:31:55.764
You didn't see that coming?

1382
01:31:57.850 --> 01:31:59.059
I'm rerouting the upload.

1383
01:32:05.941 --> 01:32:07.109
Go ahead. piss me off.

1384
01:32:19.371 --> 01:32:20.789
Wait!

1385
01:33:45.207 --> 01:33:47.543
I am sorry. That was

1386
01:33:48.502 --> 01:33:49.920
odd.

1387
01:33:50.087 --> 01:33:51.422
Thank you.

1388
01:33:56.343 --> 01:33:57.344
Thor.

1389
01:33:58.762 --> 01:33:59.805
You helped create this?

1390
01:33:59.930 --> 01:34:01.432
I've had a vision.

1391
01:34:01.557 --> 01:34:05.394
A whirlpool that sucks in all hope of life.
and at its center is that.

1392
01:34:06.311 --> 01:34:07.396
What? The gem?

1393
01:34:07.438 --> 01:34:08.522
It's the Mind Stone.

1394
01:34:08.564 --> 01:34:10.065
It's one of the six Infinity Stones.

1395
01:34:10.232 --> 01:34:11.525
The greatest power in the universe.

1396
01:34:11.567 --> 01:34:13.819
unparalleled in
its destructive capabilities.

1397
01:34:13.902 --> 01:34:15.982
- Then why would you bring...
- Because Stark is right.

1398
01:34:16.030 --> 01:34:18.532
It's definitely the end times.

1399
01:34:18.657 --> 01:34:19.742
The Avengers cannot defeat Ultron.

1400
01:34:19.825 --> 01:34:21.160
Not alone.

1401
01:34:21.618 --> 01:34:23.620
Why does your Vision
sound like Jarvis?

1402
01:34:23.704 --> 01:34:26.373
We reconfigured Jarvis's matrix

1403
01:34:26.832 --> 01:34:28.709
to create something new.

1404
01:34:28.876 --> 01:34:30.627
I think I've had my fill of new.

1405
01:34:30.711 --> 01:34:33.047
You think I'm a child of Ultron.

1406
01:34:33.339 --> 01:34:34.673
You're not?

1407
01:34:35.758 --> 01:34:37.426
I'm not Ultron.

1408
01:34:37.968 --> 01:34:40.262
I am not Jarvis. I am...

1409
01:34:42.306 --> 01:34:43.766
I am.

1410
01:34:45.601 --> 01:34:46.769
I looked in your head

1411
01:34:47.436 --> 01:34:49.271
and saw annihilation.

1412
01:34:49.438 --> 01:34:50.439
Look again.

1413
01:34:50.856 --> 01:34:52.376
Her seal of approval means jack to me.

1414
01:34:52.858 --> 01:34:55.611
Their powers. the horrors in our heads.
Ultron himself.

1415
01:34:55.694 --> 01:34:57.112
they all came from the Mind Stone.

1416
01:34:57.237 --> 01:34:59.448
And they're nothing
compared to what it can unleash.

1417
01:34:59.573 --> 01:35:01.075
- But with it on our side...
- Is it?

1418
01:35:02.493 --> 01:35:03.744
Are you?

1419
01:35:04.536 --> 01:35:05.954
On our side?

1420
01:35:07.831 --> 01:35:09.792
I don't think it's that simple.

1421
01:35:09.875 --> 01:35:12.419
Well. it better get real simple real soon.

1422
01:35:13.504 --> 01:35:15.673
I am on the side of life.

1423
01:35:15.839 --> 01:35:17.299
Ultron isn't.

1424
01:35:17.800 --> 01:35:19.301
He will end it all.

1425
01:35:19.385 --> 01:35:21.387
What's he waiting for?

1426
01:35:21.470 --> 01:35:22.471
- You.
- Where?

1427
01:35:22.888 --> 01:35:24.098
Sokovia.

1428
01:35:24.223 --> 01:35:25.307
He's got Nat there. too.

1429
01:35:27.393 --> 01:35:29.061
If we're wrong about you.

1430
01:35:31.730 --> 01:35:33.730
if you're the monster
that Ultron made you to be...

1431
01:35:34.233 --> 01:35:35.859
What will you do?

1432
01:35:42.408 --> 01:35:44.576
I don't want to kill Ultron.

1433
01:35:44.868 --> 01:35:48.288
He's unique and he's in pain.

1434
01:35:49.790 --> 01:35:52.543
But that pain will roll over the Earth.

1435
01:35:52.710 --> 01:35:55.295
So. he must be destroyed.

1436
01:35:55.421 --> 01:35:58.465
Every form he's built.
every trace of his presence on the net.

1437
01:35:58.590 --> 01:36:00.467
We have to act now.

1438
01:36:00.634 --> 01:36:04.638
And not one of us can do it
without the others.

1439
01:36:06.640 --> 01:36:08.517
Maybe I am a monster.

1440
01:36:08.684 --> 01:36:11.020
I don't think I'd know if I were one.

1441
01:36:12.146 --> 01:36:13.731
I'm not what you are.

1442
01:36:14.356 --> 01:36:16.608
and not what you intended.

1443
01:36:17.276 --> 01:36:19.820
So. there may be no way
to make you trust me.

1444
01:36:20.029 --> 01:36:21.530
But we need to go.

1445
01:36:36.253 --> 01:36:37.504
Right.

1446
01:36:38.047 --> 01:36:39.381
Well done.

1447
01:36:41.050 --> 01:36:42.092
Three minutes.

1448
01:36:42.843 --> 01:36:44.511
Get what you need.

1449
01:37:00.402 --> 01:37:01.403
<i>Good evening. boss.</i>

1450
01:37:06.533 --> 01:37:08.160
<i>No way we all get through this.</i>

1451
01:37:08.285 --> 01:37:10.365
<i>If even one tin soldier
is left standing. we've lost.</i>

1452
01:37:11.080 --> 01:37:12.520
There's gonna be blood on the floor.

1453
01:37:12.581 --> 01:37:13.957
I got no plans tomorrow night.

1454
01:37:14.041 --> 01:37:15.361
I get first crack at the big guy.

1455
01:37:15.834 --> 01:37:17.419
Iron Man's the one he's waiting for.

1456
01:37:17.461 --> 01:37:19.922
That's true. He hates you the most.

1457
01:37:25.219 --> 01:37:27.471
Ultron knows we're coming.

1458
01:37:27.596 --> 01:37:29.807
Odds are we'll be riding into heavy fire.

1459
01:37:30.307 --> 01:37:32.101
And that's what we signed up for.

1460
01:37:32.267 --> 01:37:35.104
But the people of Sokovia. they didn't.

1461
01:37:35.979 --> 01:37:37.523
<i>So our priority</i>

1462
01:37:38.148 --> 01:37:39.274
<i>is getting them out.</i>

1463
01:37:39.358 --> 01:37:42.361
We're under attack! Clear the city! Now!

1464
01:37:50.202 --> 01:37:51.745
Get off your asses.

1465
01:37:52.913 --> 01:37:54.832
<i>All they want
is to live their lives in peace.</i>

1466
01:37:55.416 --> 01:37:56.776
<i>And that's not gonna happen today.</i>

1467
01:37:58.377 --> 01:38:00.129
<i>But we can do our best to protect them.</i>

1468
01:38:00.796 --> 01:38:02.423
<i>And we can get the job done.</i>

1469
01:38:05.718 --> 01:38:08.012
<i>We find out
what Ultron's been building.</i>

1470
01:38:08.971 --> 01:38:10.639
<i>we find Romanoff.</i>

1471
01:38:11.098 --> 01:38:12.975
<i>and we clear the field.</i>

1472
01:38:14.309 --> 01:38:16.270
<i>Keep the fight between us.</i>

1473
01:38:22.985 --> 01:38:25.404
Ultron thinks we're monsters.

1474
01:38:25.904 --> 01:38:28.365
That we're what's wrong with the world.

1475
01:38:28.490 --> 01:38:30.826
This isn't just about beating him.

1476
01:38:31.285 --> 01:38:33.370
It's about whether he's right.

1477
01:38:39.793 --> 01:38:40.878
Natasha!

1478
01:38:42.004 --> 01:38:43.005
Natasha!

1479
01:38:43.088 --> 01:38:44.256
Bruce?

1480
01:38:45.549 --> 01:38:46.633
You all right?

1481
01:38:46.675 --> 01:38:47.843
Yeah.

1482
01:38:48.010 --> 01:38:49.678
The team is in the city.
It's about to light up.

1483
01:38:49.845 --> 01:38:52.005
I don't suppose you found
a key lying around somewhere.

1484
01:38:52.264 --> 01:38:54.391
Yeah. I did.

1485
01:39:00.814 --> 01:39:02.024
So what's our play?

1486
01:39:02.149 --> 01:39:03.525
I'm here to get you to safety.

1487
01:39:04.193 --> 01:39:05.194
Job's not finished.

1488
01:39:05.361 --> 01:39:08.864
We could help with the evacuation.
but I can't be in a fight near civilians.

1489
01:39:10.115 --> 01:39:11.367
And you've done plenty.

1490
01:39:13.702 --> 01:39:15.245
Our fight is over.

1491
01:39:16.580 --> 01:39:19.291
So. we just disappear?

1492
01:39:23.587 --> 01:39:25.047
Come on.

1493
01:39:29.593 --> 01:39:31.929
<i>Your man's in the church. boss.</i>

1494
01:39:32.012 --> 01:39:33.889
<i>I think he's waiting for you.</i>

1495
01:39:37.893 --> 01:39:39.937
Come to confess your sins?

1496
01:39:40.062 --> 01:39:41.397
I don't know. How much time you got?

1497
01:39:41.438 --> 01:39:43.023
More than you.

1498
01:39:45.317 --> 01:39:48.195
Have you been juicing?
Little vibranium cocktail?

1499
01:39:48.237 --> 01:39:50.572
You're looking...
I don't wanna say "puffy."

1500
01:39:50.739 --> 01:39:52.408
You're stalling to protect the people.

1501
01:39:52.783 --> 01:39:55.786
Well. that is the mission.
Did you forget?

1502
01:39:55.911 --> 01:39:58.414
I've moved beyond your mission.
I'm free.

1503
01:40:03.210 --> 01:40:04.294
What?

1504
01:40:05.129 --> 01:40:07.548
You think you were
the only one stalling?

1505
01:40:08.257 --> 01:40:09.883
<i>There's the rest of the vibranium.</i>

1506
01:40:09.925 --> 01:40:11.427
<i>Function. still unclear.</i>

1507
01:40:11.552 --> 01:40:13.262
This is how you end. Tony.

1508
01:40:13.971 --> 01:40:15.764
This is peace in my time.

1509
01:40:32.448 --> 01:40:33.490
Go!

1510
01:40:38.996 --> 01:40:40.414
Get off the bridge!

1511
01:40:44.626 --> 01:40:45.627
Run!

1512
01:40:47.588 --> 01:40:49.340
Ultron.

1513
01:40:54.845 --> 01:40:56.180
My Vision.

1514
01:40:56.305 --> 01:40:58.599
They really did take
everything from me.

1515
01:40:58.724 --> 01:41:00.851
You set the terms.
You can change them.

1516
01:41:00.976 --> 01:41:02.186
All right.

1517
01:41:26.335 --> 01:41:27.586
Friday. the Vision?

1518
01:41:27.670 --> 01:41:28.712
<i>Boss. it's working.</i>

1519
01:41:28.796 --> 01:41:31.396
<i>He's burning Ultron out of the net.
He won't escape through there.</i>

1520
01:41:36.095 --> 01:41:37.513
You shut me out.

1521
01:41:38.013 --> 01:41:39.306
You think I care?

1522
01:41:41.225 --> 01:41:42.434
You take away my world.

1523
01:41:43.310 --> 01:41:45.229
I take away yours.

1524
01:42:29.565 --> 01:42:30.858
Friday.

1525
01:42:30.899 --> 01:42:33.402
<i>Sokovia is going for a ride.</i>

1526
01:42:45.831 --> 01:42:47.374
Do you see

1527
01:42:47.791 --> 01:42:49.418
the beauty of it?

1528
01:42:49.918 --> 01:42:51.920
The inevitability.

1529
01:42:52.004 --> 01:42:55.341
You rise. only to fall.

1530
01:42:58.052 --> 01:43:01.722
<i>You. Avengers. you are my meteor.</i>

1531
01:43:01.764 --> 01:43:03.515
<i>My swift and terrible sword.</i>

1532
01:43:03.724 --> 01:43:05.267
<i>And the earth will crack</i>

1533
01:43:05.392 --> 01:43:07.269
<i>with the weight of your failure.</i>

1534
01:43:08.979 --> 01:43:12.775
<i>Purge me from your computers.
turn my own flesh against me.</i>

1535
01:43:13.067 --> 01:43:14.151
<i>It means nothing.</i>

1536
01:43:14.777 --> 01:43:16.528
<i>When the dust settles.</i>

1537
01:43:16.612 --> 01:43:18.572
<i>the only thing living in this world</i>

1538
01:43:19.573 --> 01:43:20.616
<i>will be metal.</i>

1539
01:43:25.454 --> 01:43:26.789
We gotta move.

1540
01:43:27.122 --> 01:43:28.242
You're not gonna turn green?

1541
01:43:28.374 --> 01:43:31.085
I've got a compelling reason
not to lose my cool.

1542
01:43:31.377 --> 01:43:32.378
I adore you.

1543
01:43:41.387 --> 01:43:43.555
But I need the other guy.

1544
01:43:48.143 --> 01:43:49.978
Let's finish the job.

1545
01:44:06.704 --> 01:44:08.080
I really hope this makes us even.

1546
01:44:10.416 --> 01:44:11.417
Now go be a hero.

1547
01:44:20.926 --> 01:44:22.928
<i>The vibranium core's
got a magnetic field.</i>

1548
01:44:23.053 --> 01:44:25.055
<i>That's what's keeping
the rock together.</i>

1549
01:44:25.180 --> 01:44:26.181
If it drops?

1550
01:44:26.265 --> 01:44:27.599
<i>Right now.
the impact will kill thousands.</i>

1551
01:44:27.683 --> 01:44:30.352
<i>Once it gets high enough?
Global extinction.</i>

1552
01:44:34.690 --> 01:44:36.859
<i>That building's not clear.
The 10th floor.</i>

1553
01:44:41.655 --> 01:44:42.656
Hi.

1554
01:44:43.782 --> 01:44:45.075
Okay.

1555
01:44:45.159 --> 01:44:46.160
Get in the tub!

1556
01:44:53.000 --> 01:44:54.835
<i>I got airborne.
heading up to the bridge.</i>

1557
01:44:57.588 --> 01:44:58.881
Cap. you got incoming.

1558
01:44:59.048 --> 01:45:00.674
Incoming already came in.

1559
01:45:03.344 --> 01:45:05.804
Stark. you worry about
bringing the city back down safely.

1560
01:45:06.472 --> 01:45:08.265
<i>The rest of us have one job.</i>

1561
01:45:08.390 --> 01:45:09.641
<i>tear these things apart.</i>

1562
01:45:09.933 --> 01:45:11.602
<i>You get hurt. hurt them back.</i>

1563
01:45:12.227 --> 01:45:13.395
<i>You get killed.</i>

1564
01:45:14.396 --> 01:45:15.731
walk it off.

1565
01:45:50.349 --> 01:45:51.350
Go. go. go!

1566
01:45:57.022 --> 01:45:58.774
How could I let this happen?

1567
01:45:58.941 --> 01:45:59.942
Hey. hey. you okay?

1568
01:46:00.025 --> 01:46:01.068
This is all our fault.

1569
01:46:01.110 --> 01:46:02.111
Hey. look at me.

1570
01:46:02.194 --> 01:46:04.488
It's your fault. it's everyone's fault.
Who cares?

1571
01:46:04.571 --> 01:46:06.073
Are you up for this?

1572
01:46:06.198 --> 01:46:07.199
Are you?

1573
01:46:07.783 --> 01:46:10.953
Look. I just need to know.
Because the city is flying.

1574
01:46:11.245 --> 01:46:15.165
Okay. Look. the city is flying.
we're fighting an army of robots.

1575
01:46:16.000 --> 01:46:17.292
and I have a bow and arrow.

1576
01:46:17.376 --> 01:46:18.502
None of this makes sense.

1577
01:46:21.755 --> 01:46:23.841
But I'm going back out there
because it's my job.

1578
01:46:24.717 --> 01:46:27.469
Okay? And I can't do my job
and babysit.

1579
01:46:27.511 --> 01:46:30.639
It doesn't matter what you did
or what you were.

1580
01:46:30.806 --> 01:46:33.308
If you go out there. you fight.
and you fight to kill.

1581
01:46:34.351 --> 01:46:36.991
Stay in here. you're good.
I'll send your brother to come find you.

1582
01:46:37.062 --> 01:46:38.939
But if you step out that door.

1583
01:46:39.815 --> 01:46:40.858
you are an Avenger.

1584
01:46:45.696 --> 01:46:47.531
All right. Good chat.

1585
01:46:51.285 --> 01:46:52.327
Yeah. the city is flying.

1586
01:47:26.320 --> 01:47:27.446
I got you!

1587
01:47:27.821 --> 01:47:29.073
Just look at me!

1588
01:47:35.829 --> 01:47:37.164
<i>You can't save them all.</i>

1589
01:47:38.624 --> 01:47:39.625
You'll never...

1590
01:47:40.626 --> 01:47:41.627
"Never" what?

1591
01:47:41.919 --> 01:47:43.212
You didn't finish!

1592
01:47:46.965 --> 01:47:48.592
What. were you napping?

1593
01:48:10.072 --> 01:48:11.073
Thor.

1594
01:48:13.742 --> 01:48:15.285
You're bothering me.

1595
01:48:50.696 --> 01:48:51.947
All right. we're all clear here.

1596
01:48:51.989 --> 01:48:53.157
We are not clear!

1597
01:48:53.240 --> 01:48:54.700
We are very not clear!

1598
01:48:57.536 --> 01:48:58.537
All right. coming to you.

1599
01:48:59.496 --> 01:49:00.831
Keep up. old man!

1600
01:49:03.334 --> 01:49:04.918
Nobody would know.

1601
01:49:05.669 --> 01:49:06.795
Nobody.

1602
01:49:08.630 --> 01:49:11.633
"The last I saw him.
an Ultron was sitting on him.

1603
01:49:11.800 --> 01:49:13.635
"Yeah. he'll be missed.
that quick little bastard.

1604
01:49:13.719 --> 01:49:14.720
"I miss him already."

1605
01:49:30.235 --> 01:49:31.445
Hold your fire!

1606
01:49:41.330 --> 01:49:42.331
Romanoff!

1607
01:49:42.831 --> 01:49:43.874
Thanks!

1608
01:49:53.258 --> 01:49:54.927
<i>The anti-gravs are rigged to flip.</i>

1609
01:49:55.010 --> 01:49:57.221
<i>Touch them.
they'll go full reverse thrust.</i>

1610
01:49:57.304 --> 01:49:58.764
<i>The city's not coming down slow.</i>

1611
01:49:58.847 --> 01:49:59.890
Spire is vibranium.

1612
01:49:59.973 --> 01:50:01.350
If I get Thor to hit it...

1613
01:50:01.433 --> 01:50:02.893
<i>It will crack. That's not enough.</i>

1614
01:50:02.976 --> 01:50:04.520
<i>The impact would still be devastating.</i>

1615
01:50:04.603 --> 01:50:05.963
Maybe if we can cap the other end.

1616
01:50:06.188 --> 01:50:07.856
Keep the atomic action doubling back.

1617
01:50:07.940 --> 01:50:09.274
<i>That could vaporize the city.</i>

1618
01:50:10.275 --> 01:50:12.194
<i>And everyone on it.</i>

1619
01:50:17.991 --> 01:50:19.868
The next wave is gonna hit any minute.

1620
01:50:19.952 --> 01:50:21.870
- What do you got. Stark?
<i>- Nothing great.</i>

1621
01:50:22.746 --> 01:50:25.040
Maybe a way to blow up the city.

1622
01:50:25.082 --> 01:50:26.458
That'll keep it
from impacting the surface.

1623
01:50:26.542 --> 01:50:27.626
if you guys can get clear.

1624
01:50:27.793 --> 01:50:29.670
I asked for a solution.
not an escape plan.

1625
01:50:29.795 --> 01:50:32.881
<i>Impact radius
is getting bigger every second.</i>

1626
01:50:33.048 --> 01:50:34.408
<i>We're gonna have to make a choice.</i>

1627
01:50:35.050 --> 01:50:36.719
Cap. these people are going nowhere.

1628
01:50:37.469 --> 01:50:38.929
If Stark finds a way to blow this rock...

1629
01:50:39.013 --> 01:50:40.014
Not till everyone's safe.

1630
01:50:40.723 --> 01:50:43.767
Everyone up here versus everyone
down there? There's no math there.

1631
01:50:43.892 --> 01:50:45.686
I'm not leaving this rock
with one civilian on it.

1632
01:50:45.811 --> 01:50:47.312
I didn't say we should leave.

1633
01:50:50.232 --> 01:50:52.109
There's worse ways to go.

1634
01:50:57.489 --> 01:50:59.992
Where else am I gonna get
a view like this?

1635
01:51:00.868 --> 01:51:03.412
<i>Glad you like the view. Romanoff.</i>

1636
01:51:03.579 --> 01:51:05.080
<i>It's about to get better.</i>

1637
01:51:29.271 --> 01:51:30.439
<i>Nice. right?</i>

1638
01:51:30.606 --> 01:51:33.108
Pulled her out of mothballs
with a couple of old friends.

1639
01:51:33.150 --> 01:51:34.777
She's dusty. but she'll do.

1640
01:51:35.152 --> 01:51:36.612
Fury. you son of a bitch.

1641
01:51:36.945 --> 01:51:39.114
You kiss your mother with that mouth?

1642
01:51:39.239 --> 01:51:41.492
Altitude is 18.000 and climbing.

1643
01:51:41.617 --> 01:51:43.118
Lifeboats secure to deploy.

1644
01:51:43.160 --> 01:51:45.913
Disengage in three. two...

1645
01:51:47.081 --> 01:51:48.082
Take them out.

1646
01:51:57.716 --> 01:51:59.343
This is S.H.I.E.L.D.?

1647
01:51:59.426 --> 01:52:01.887
This is what S.H.I.E.L.D.
is supposed to be.

1648
01:52:03.472 --> 01:52:04.932
This is not so bad.

1649
01:52:08.185 --> 01:52:09.520
Let's load them up.

1650
01:52:14.942 --> 01:52:18.821
Sir. we have multiple bogies
converging on our starboard flank.

1651
01:52:19.113 --> 01:52:20.322
Show 'em what we got.

1652
01:52:20.739 --> 01:52:21.740
You're up.

1653
01:52:26.954 --> 01:52:27.996
Yes!

1654
01:52:28.163 --> 01:52:29.957
Now this is gonna be a good story.

1655
01:52:32.584 --> 01:52:34.670
Yup. If you live to tell it.

1656
01:52:34.795 --> 01:52:36.880
You think I can't hold my own?

1657
01:52:36.964 --> 01:52:38.564
We get through this. I'll hold your own.

1658
01:52:38.632 --> 01:52:40.551
You had to make it weird.

1659
01:52:45.347 --> 01:52:48.350
I got about 50 to 100 more
coming in after this group.

1660
01:53:05.200 --> 01:53:06.702
Here we go. Here we go. Let's move.

1661
01:53:07.077 --> 01:53:08.078
Let's go. everyone!

1662
01:53:10.581 --> 01:53:12.666
Number six boat is topped and locked...

1663
01:53:12.708 --> 01:53:15.169
Or stocked... Topped...

1664
01:53:15.669 --> 01:53:17.087
It's full of people.

1665
01:53:18.839 --> 01:53:19.923
Incoming!

1666
01:53:22.926 --> 01:53:24.053
Oh. God!

1667
01:53:34.521 --> 01:53:35.773
<i>You think you're saving anyone?</i>

1668
01:53:37.608 --> 01:53:39.943
I turn that key
and drop this rock a little early

1669
01:53:40.027 --> 01:53:41.904
and it's still billions dead.

1670
01:53:42.321 --> 01:53:43.447
Even you can't stop that.

1671
01:53:43.572 --> 01:53:46.200
I am Thor. son of Odin.

1672
01:53:46.241 --> 01:53:48.494
and as long as there is life
in my breast...

1673
01:53:48.660 --> 01:53:51.080
I am running out of things to say!

1674
01:53:51.163 --> 01:53:52.164
Are you ready?

1675
01:53:59.838 --> 01:54:00.964
It's terribly well-balanced.

1676
01:54:01.340 --> 01:54:04.843
Well. if there's too much weight.
you lose power on the swing. so...

1677
01:54:05.761 --> 01:54:08.472
I got it. Create a heat seal.

1678
01:54:08.847 --> 01:54:09.848
I could...

1679
01:54:09.973 --> 01:54:12.351
I could supercharge
the spire from below.

1680
01:54:12.476 --> 01:54:13.727
<i>Running numbers.</i>

1681
01:54:23.737 --> 01:54:25.781
<i>A heat seal could work
with enough power.</i>

1682
01:54:25.864 --> 01:54:27.866
- Thor. I got a plan.
<i>- We're out of time.</i>

1683
01:54:27.991 --> 01:54:29.326
<i>They're coming for the core.</i>

1684
01:54:29.410 --> 01:54:31.286
Rhodey. get the rest of the people
on board that carrier.

1685
01:54:31.328 --> 01:54:32.329
On it.

1686
01:54:32.413 --> 01:54:34.623
Avengers. time to work for a living.

1687
01:54:43.632 --> 01:54:44.967
- Are you good?
- Yeah.

1688
01:54:46.385 --> 01:54:47.469
Romanoff.

1689
01:54:47.636 --> 01:54:50.139
You and Banner better not be
playing "hide the zucchini."

1690
01:54:50.180 --> 01:54:51.181
<i>Relax. shellhead.</i>

1691
01:54:51.515 --> 01:54:53.058
Not all of us can fly.

1692
01:54:58.731 --> 01:55:00.482
- What's the drill?
- This is the drill.

1693
01:55:00.566 --> 01:55:02.776
If Ultron gets a hand
on the core. we lose.

1694
01:55:07.322 --> 01:55:09.324
Is that the best you can do?

1695
01:55:19.209 --> 01:55:20.753
You had to ask.

1696
01:55:20.878 --> 01:55:23.297
This is the best I can do.

1697
01:55:23.339 --> 01:55:25.007
This is exactly what I wanted.

1698
01:55:25.341 --> 01:55:26.675
All of you

1699
01:55:26.842 --> 01:55:28.510
against all of me.

1700
01:55:28.677 --> 01:55:30.888
How can you possibly hope to stop me?

1701
01:55:31.680 --> 01:55:33.640
Well. like the old man said...

1702
01:55:34.933 --> 01:55:35.976
Together.

1703
01:57:04.898 --> 01:57:07.317
You know.
with the benefit of hindsight...

1704
01:57:16.493 --> 01:57:17.619
They'll try to leave the city.

1705
01:57:17.703 --> 01:57:19.413
We can't let them.
not even one. Rhodey.

1706
01:57:19.830 --> 01:57:20.831
I'm on it.

1707
01:57:21.248 --> 01:57:22.624
No. I didn't say you could leave.

1708
01:57:23.208 --> 01:57:25.377
War Machine coming at you! Right...

1709
01:57:31.675 --> 01:57:33.135
Okay. what?

1710
01:57:33.302 --> 01:57:35.387
We gotta move out.
Even I can tell the air is getting thin.

1711
01:57:35.471 --> 01:57:36.805
You guys get to the boats.

1712
01:57:36.889 --> 01:57:38.729
I'll sweep for stragglers.
Be right behind you.

1713
01:57:38.807 --> 01:57:40.225
What about the core?

1714
01:57:40.392 --> 01:57:41.393
I'll protect it.

1715
01:57:43.312 --> 01:57:44.313
It's my job.

1716
01:57:45.522 --> 01:57:46.523
Nat.

1717
01:57:46.857 --> 01:57:47.900
This way.

1718
01:57:52.279 --> 01:57:53.572
Get the people on the boats.

1719
01:57:53.655 --> 01:57:54.656
I'm not going to leave you here.

1720
01:57:54.740 --> 01:57:55.866
I can handle this.

1721
01:57:58.118 --> 01:57:59.411
Come back for me
when everyone else is off.

1722
01:57:59.536 --> 01:58:00.704
Not before.

1723
01:58:01.288 --> 01:58:02.831
You understand?

1724
01:58:03.832 --> 01:58:05.542
You know.
I'm 12 minutes older than you.

1725
01:58:05.751 --> 01:58:07.044
Go.

1726
01:58:08.629 --> 01:58:10.172
<i>Boss. power levels are way below...</i>

1727
01:58:10.214 --> 01:58:12.424
Reroute everything.
We get one shot at this.

1728
01:58:17.304 --> 01:58:18.639
I know what I need to do.

1729
01:58:18.931 --> 01:58:20.015
The dining room.

1730
01:58:20.307 --> 01:58:21.517
If I knock out that east wall.

1731
01:58:22.184 --> 01:58:23.824
it'd make a nice workspace
for Laura. huh?

1732
01:58:25.270 --> 01:58:26.522
Put up some baffling.

1733
01:58:26.563 --> 01:58:28.691
She can't hear the kids running around.
What do you think?

1734
01:58:28.774 --> 01:58:30.067
You guys always eat
in the kitchen anyway.

1735
01:58:30.150 --> 01:58:31.735
No one eats in a dining room.

1736
01:58:37.408 --> 01:58:38.528
We don't have a lot of time.

1737
01:58:39.034 --> 01:58:41.078
So get your ass on a boat.

1738
01:58:53.966 --> 01:58:55.175
Hey. big guy.

1739
01:58:56.885 --> 01:58:58.679
Sun's getting real low.

1740
01:58:59.221 --> 01:59:01.890
You're safe now.
You're gonna be okay. Buckle up.

1741
01:59:04.393 --> 01:59:06.020
Secure your gear. find a seat.

1742
01:59:06.061 --> 01:59:07.396
Costel!

1743
01:59:08.397 --> 01:59:09.648
We were in the market.

1744
01:59:09.773 --> 01:59:10.816
Costel!

1745
01:59:25.414 --> 01:59:27.458
Thor. I'm gonna need you
back in the church.

1746
01:59:27.624 --> 01:59:29.084
- Is this the last of them?
- Yeah.

1747
01:59:29.460 --> 01:59:30.502
Everyone else is on the carrier.

1748
01:59:30.586 --> 01:59:31.754
<i>You know. this works.</i>

1749
01:59:32.379 --> 01:59:33.756
we maybe don't walk away.

1750
01:59:34.465 --> 01:59:35.549
Maybe not.

1751
01:59:54.693 --> 01:59:58.280
<i>I got no strings. so I have fun</i>

1752
01:59:58.697 --> 02:00:01.492
<i>I'm not tied up to anyone</i>

1753
02:00:02.951 --> 02:00:04.328
Come on. Time to go.

1754
02:00:36.777 --> 02:00:38.862
You didn't see that coming?

1755
02:01:35.044 --> 02:01:36.879
For God's sake.

1756
02:01:53.062 --> 02:01:54.938
- Zrinka!
- Costel! Baby!

1757
02:02:07.326 --> 02:02:08.369
No. no. I'm fine.

1758
02:02:08.494 --> 02:02:09.578
Fine.

1759
02:02:11.413 --> 02:02:13.499
It's been a long day.

1760
02:02:27.971 --> 02:02:29.264
Wanda.

1761
02:02:29.932 --> 02:02:33.227
If you stay here. you'll die.

1762
02:02:34.728 --> 02:02:36.188
I just did.

1763
02:02:36.939 --> 02:02:38.649
Do you know how it felt?

1764
02:02:52.788 --> 02:02:55.082
It felt like that.

1765
02:03:30.075 --> 02:03:31.744
Thor. on my mark.

1766
02:03:46.842 --> 02:03:47.843
Now!

1767
02:04:15.871 --> 02:04:18.248
<i>Hey. big guy. We did it.</i>

1768
02:04:19.291 --> 02:04:20.959
<i>The job is finished.</i>

1769
02:04:21.210 --> 02:04:23.879
<i>Now I need you to turn
this bird around. okay?</i>

1770
02:04:28.133 --> 02:04:29.968
We can't track you in stealth mode.

1771
02:04:32.054 --> 02:04:34.306
<i>So help me out. I need you...</i>

1772
02:05:19.893 --> 02:05:20.978
You're afraid.

1773
02:05:21.895 --> 02:05:22.938
Of you?

1774
02:05:23.647 --> 02:05:24.898
Of death.

1775
02:05:25.524 --> 02:05:27.401
You're the last one.

1776
02:05:27.568 --> 02:05:30.112
You were supposed to be the last.

1777
02:05:30.279 --> 02:05:32.614
Stark asked for a savior

1778
02:05:33.532 --> 02:05:35.284
and settled for a slave.

1779
02:05:35.367 --> 02:05:37.870
I suppose we are both disappointments.

1780
02:05:40.205 --> 02:05:41.457
I suppose we are.

1781
02:05:42.207 --> 02:05:43.375
Humans are odd.

1782
02:05:45.210 --> 02:05:48.922
They think order and chaos
are somehow opposites

1783
02:05:50.591 --> 02:05:51.967
and try to control what won't be.

1784
02:05:53.635 --> 02:05:56.138
But there is grace in their failings.

1785
02:05:56.472 --> 02:05:58.432
I think you missed that.

1786
02:05:59.016 --> 02:06:00.184
They're doomed.

1787
02:06:01.018 --> 02:06:02.144
Yes.

1788
02:06:06.273 --> 02:06:09.276
But a thing isn't beautiful
because it lasts.

1789
02:06:11.278 --> 02:06:13.364
It's a privilege to be among them.

1790
02:06:13.489 --> 02:06:16.116
You're unbearably naive.

1791
02:06:16.325 --> 02:06:17.618
Well...

1792
02:06:19.620 --> 02:06:21.747
I was born yesterday.

1793
02:07:11.839 --> 02:07:15.884
New Avengers Facility
Upstate New York

1794
02:07:34.236 --> 02:07:35.320
<i>Look! Say hi to Auntie Nat!</i>

1795
02:07:37.740 --> 02:07:38.824
Fat.

1796
02:07:39.908 --> 02:07:41.268
One of our tech boys flagged this.

1797
02:07:42.161 --> 02:07:44.455
Splashed down in the Banda Sea.

1798
02:07:45.622 --> 02:07:47.124
Could be the Quinjet.

1799
02:07:47.499 --> 02:07:50.919
But with Stark's stealth tech.
we still can't track the damn thing.

1800
02:07:52.421 --> 02:07:53.839
Right.

1801
02:07:54.214 --> 02:07:56.467
Probably jumped out and swam to Fiji.

1802
02:07:57.760 --> 02:07:59.678
He'll send a postcard.

1803
02:07:59.928 --> 02:08:01.680
"Wish you were here."

1804
02:08:03.599 --> 02:08:06.810
You sent me to recruit him
way back when.

1805
02:08:08.687 --> 02:08:11.273
Did you know then
what was gonna happen?

1806
02:08:13.442 --> 02:08:15.444
You never know.

1807
02:08:15.611 --> 02:08:19.114
You hope for the best.
then make do with what you get.

1808
02:08:19.573 --> 02:08:20.991
I got a great team.

1809
02:08:22.159 --> 02:08:24.161
Nothing lasts forever.

1810
02:08:24.453 --> 02:08:26.538
Trouble. Ms. Romanoff.

1811
02:08:26.705 --> 02:08:30.042
No matter who wins or loses.
trouble still comes around.

1812
02:08:33.962 --> 02:08:35.214
<i>The rules have changed.</i>

1813
02:08:35.339 --> 02:08:36.924
We're dealing with something new.

1814
02:08:37.049 --> 02:08:38.467
The Vision is artificial intelligence.

1815
02:08:38.509 --> 02:08:40.511
- A machine.
- So. it doesn't count?

1816
02:08:40.594 --> 02:08:42.394
No. it's not like
a person lifting the hammer.

1817
02:08:42.680 --> 02:08:44.431
Right. different rules for us.

1818
02:08:44.473 --> 02:08:45.516
- Nice guy. Artificial.
- Thank you.

1819
02:08:45.641 --> 02:08:48.602
He can wield the hammer.
he can keep the Mind Stone.

1820
02:08:49.603 --> 02:08:51.772
It's safe with the Vision.

1821
02:08:51.939 --> 02:08:54.483
And these days. safe is in short supply.

1822
02:08:56.485 --> 02:08:58.487
But if you put the hammer
in an elevator...

1823
02:08:58.612 --> 02:09:00.412
- It would still go up.
- Elevator's not worthy.

1824
02:09:00.489 --> 02:09:02.366
I'm gonna miss these little talks of ours.

1825
02:09:02.449 --> 02:09:04.118
Not if you don't leave.

1826
02:09:04.159 --> 02:09:06.036
I have no choice.

1827
02:09:06.161 --> 02:09:08.372
The Mind Stone is the fourth
of the Infinity Stones

1828
02:09:08.497 --> 02:09:09.873
to show up in the last few years.

1829
02:09:09.998 --> 02:09:11.625
It's not a coincidence.

1830
02:09:12.376 --> 02:09:14.211
Someone has been playing
an intricate game

1831
02:09:14.294 --> 02:09:16.005
and has made pawns of us.

1832
02:09:16.046 --> 02:09:17.923
And once all these pieces
are in position...

1833
02:09:18.048 --> 02:09:19.550
Triple Yahtzee.

1834
02:09:19.675 --> 02:09:21.135
You think you can find out
what's coming?

1835
02:09:21.260 --> 02:09:22.344
I do.

1836
02:09:23.095 --> 02:09:24.680
Besides this one.

1837
02:09:24.763 --> 02:09:27.099
there's nothing that can't be explained.

1838
02:09:34.440 --> 02:09:36.984
That man has no regard
for lawn maintenance.

1839
02:09:40.112 --> 02:09:42.823
I'm gonna miss him. though.
And you're gonna miss me.

1840
02:09:42.865 --> 02:09:44.616
There's gonna be a lot of manful tears.

1841
02:09:46.618 --> 02:09:48.370
I will miss you. Tony.

1842
02:09:48.537 --> 02:09:49.538
Yeah?

1843
02:09:49.663 --> 02:09:52.249
Well. it's time for me to tap out.

1844
02:09:52.332 --> 02:09:54.585
Maybe I should take a page
out of Barton's book.

1845
02:09:54.668 --> 02:09:57.671
Build Pepper a farm.
hope nobody blows it up.

1846
02:09:58.297 --> 02:09:59.548
The simple life.

1847
02:09:59.715 --> 02:10:01.050
You'll get there one day.

1848
02:10:01.091 --> 02:10:02.092
I don't know.

1849
02:10:02.343 --> 02:10:04.803
Family. stability...

1850
02:10:05.888 --> 02:10:09.099
The guy who wanted all that
went in the ice 75 years ago.

1851
02:10:10.517 --> 02:10:12.394
I think someone else came out.

1852
02:10:16.440 --> 02:10:17.441
You all right?

1853
02:10:20.110 --> 02:10:21.570
I'm home.

1854
02:10:29.453 --> 02:10:32.247
You wanna keep staring at the wall.
or do you wanna go to work?

1855
02:10:32.414 --> 02:10:33.791
I mean. it's a pretty interesting wall.

1856
02:10:33.874 --> 02:10:36.960
I thought you and Tony were
still gazing into each other's eyes.

1857
02:10:37.044 --> 02:10:38.045
How do we look?

1858
02:10:38.253 --> 02:10:40.589
Well. we're not the '27 Yankees.

1859
02:10:40.673 --> 02:10:42.466
We got some hitters.

1860
02:10:42.549 --> 02:10:45.052
They're good. They're not a team.

1861
02:10:45.094 --> 02:10:46.720
Let's beat them into shape.

1862
02:11:05.197 --> 02:11:06.824
Avengers...

1863
02:13:25.587 --> 02:13:27.089
Fine.

1864
02:13:28.465 --> 02:13:29.545
I'll do it myself.

1865
02:13:32.048 --> 02:21:04.037
Subtitles by <font color="#aa0000">Doctor xNo</font>
https://cryptovision.live
